title: fancy salsa dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Grate Cheddar cheese. Put all 3 ingredients into mixing bowl and beat until well blended. Chill 1 hour or longer. Serve with tortilla chips or on crackers.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine pie filling, milk, vanilla and 1/2 of the whipped topping; mix on low speed until blended. Increase speed and beat until thick, about 2 minutes. Pour 1/3 of mixture into crust. Layer bananas on top, reserving 1/2 banana for garnish. Pour remaining filling into crust. Chill 2 hours. Garnish with remaining bananas, whipped topping and optional chocolate sundae syrup.

title: cheese corn mini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

In a large bowl, combine corn meal, flour, cheese, sugar, peppers, baking powder and salt; mix well. In another bowl, beat together the sour cream, eggs and butter. Stir in the dry ingredients; mix well.
Put into mini muffin pans, filling cups almost to the top.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden.
Cool in pans on a wire rack for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 36.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Thicken 1 large can crushed pineapple with flour. Add sugar; set aside and allow to cool. Into pie shells, slice bananas; cover with coconut. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Pour cooled pineapple mixture over this. Top with whipped cream.

title: broiled lamb parisienne
directions: Mix olive oil or salad oil, lemon juice and salad dressing mix in a large shallow glass dish; place lamb in marinade, turning to coat well; cover.
Chill, turning meat every few hours, for 12 hours or overnight to season.
About 1/2 hour before serving, remove lamb from marinade and place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 15 minutes; turn.
Broil 15 minutes longer, or until richly browned and crispy at edges.
Place on a cutting board; carve into 1/4-inch slices.
(Thicker parts will be pink inside and thin ones well done).
Serve with Skillet Tomato Bouquets.

title: noodles
directions: Put eggs in mixing bowl and beat.
Put dry ingredients into sifter and sift into eggs.
Pour in melted butter.
Roll out, cut and let set 1/2 to 1 hour.
Don't bunch up, will not dry out. Cook noodles in your favorite boiling broth.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pumpkin cookie faces
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Stir in pumpkin and molasses. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices; blend into pumpkin mixture. Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours. Preheat oven to 375°. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured cloth-covered board. Cut with floured pumpkin-shaped cookie cutter. Gently place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until firm to the touch. Cool on wire racks. Decorate as desired. Makes 2 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Grease a square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat corn syrup and margarine to boiling in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla; stir in cereal gradually until completely coated with chocolate.
Pour in marshmallows.
Pour cereal mixture into pan and press with the back of buttered spoon. Let cool for about one hour.
Makes about 24 bars.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make meatballs and brown them.
Drain off fat.
Melt jelly in cocktail sauce over medium heat.
Put meatballs in sauce and cook about 1/2 hour.
Good served over rice.

title: sopaipilla
directions: Step 1:
Cut tortilla in tiny pizza shapes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Slice vegetables thick.
Layer in casserole, beginning and ending with hamburger.
Mix soup; heat and stir well.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 275° or 300° for 1 1/2 hours, or until well done.

title: sausage rice
directions: Pour in large casserole.
Add to casserole 1 1/3 cups raw long grain rice.
Pour 2 cans of chicken broth.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Boil slowly 10 minutes.
Stir in egg yolk and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add lemon juices and rind.
Fill baked crust; cover with meringue. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Can use whipped cream instead of meringue.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add cheese; stir until it melts.
Add seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Spread on bread while warm.
Place under broiler for a few minutes before serving.
These are excellent to make and freeze ahead of time.
They can also be put on regular rye and used for a meal.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Season with salt.
Place ham and cheese stick on each breast and roll up and tie.
Coat rolls with flour and lightly brown in butter.
Place in baking dish.
In same skillet, stir in mushrooms, water, wine and Heinz 57 sauce.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Thicken sauce if desired.
Serve with rice.
Great for company!

title: acapulco gold cake
directions: Grease and flour the bottom of a tube cake pan.
Melt chocolate and water together until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Blend in cream.
(I use microwave to melt chocolate; may use double boiler.) Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and shortening until blended.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine milk and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients.
Turn 1/4 of the batter into pan, then drizzle 1/2 chocolate mixture on top of batter.
Repeat, ending with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.
May take up to 80 minutes.
(Check at 45 minutes.)
Serves up to 20.

title: jean's corn casserole
directions: Mix all together in 13 x 9-inch pan; top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced coffee
directions: Right before serving the coffee, pour it into a microwave-proof pitcher.
Stir in the orange peel, cinnamon and allspice.
Heat the coffee on High for 1 to 3 minutes, or until heated through.

title: tropical sunny sherbet slush
directions: In large punch bowl, mix together all ingredients in order and stir.
Makes 14 1/2 (8 ounce) glasses.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening. Beat with mixer until smooth; do not overbeat.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been lightly greased or sprayed with Pam. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Congeal in fridge.
Reserve other half at room temperature.
Spread sour cream over congealed mixture.
Pour the rest of jello mixture over.
Put back in fridge and congeal.

title: rolls
directions: Add yeast to water; add sugar and oil.
Fold in flour.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Spread each roll with melted butter.
Can be baked at once, but better if let set for 1 hour in a warm place.
Bake in a 400° oven.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make a paste with vinegar and cocoa; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, and beat until fluffy.
Add vinegar and cocoa.
Sift flour, salt and soda together; add to batter.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and food coloring.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cake is done when it springs back when touched.

title: dilly cucumber salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine sour cream, lemon, sugar, salt and dill weed.
Mix well.
Add cucumber and onion.
Chill to blend flavors.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions except use broth leftover from boiling the chicken.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add Marshmallow Creme and beat until smooth.
Add peanut butter.

title: super easy hoisin chicken
directions: Combine shoyu sauce, sugar, water and hoisin sauce.
Soak chicken for 2 hours or overnight.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix Cool Whip, Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add fruit and stir until blended.
Chill.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Salt and pepper the prepared chicken breast.
Place in shallow baking pan and spread thickly with sour cream.
Sprinkle the dry dressing heavily over all.
Dot well with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes until crisp and brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cool rhubarb and 1/2 cup water as for sauce.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Pour into hot sterilized glasses.
Add paraffin. Seal.

title: banana, strawberry, rum smoothie
directions: Blend until smooth.
Yields about 16 ounces.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill at least one day before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt together.
Add boiling water while stirring constantly, using high heat until mixture begins to thicken, then cook slowly on low heat until thick.
Add beaten eggs and cook 2 minutes longer.
Add lemon juice and rind. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell (9-inch).
Cover with meringue if desired.

title: barbecue flank steak
directions: Rub both sides of the steak with pepper.
In a shallow dish, just large enough to hold the steak, whisk together the oil, lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic.
Add the steak, coating both sides well with the marinade.
Let it marinate for 20 minutes, turning it once.
Remove the steak from marinade and grill it on an oiled rack over glowing coals, brushing it occasionally with the marinade and turning it once for 10 to 12 minutes for medium-rare meat.

title: spicy snack
directions: Bring 1 quart of water to boiling.
Dump almonds in boiling water; cook about 1 minute.
Drain almonds well in a colander. Heat the oil in a nonstick skillet.
Add cayenne pepper and salt to the hot oil.
Saute almonds until golden.
Cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cake
directions: Mix cake mix, water, oil, egg whites or whole eggs together. Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan with shortening; lightly flour or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake as directed.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean or cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cool cake.
Put on the pie filling.
Then put on the vanilla frosting and put on coconut flakes.

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Rinse in cold water; drain on paper towels.
Melt butter in saucepan; add garlic and cook on medium heat for 1 minute.

title: fresh spring pea soup
directions: Melt the butter (or brown the pork).
Saute the diced potato for a couple of minutes.
Add chicken broth and simmer until potatoes are soft (about 20 minutes).
Bring to a boil and add the green peas.
As soon as peas are tender, stir in chives and serve immediately.

title: baked apples supreme
directions: Slice apples in half roundwise.
Core but do not cut through to bottom so they will hold filling.
Bring sugar, water, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg to a boil and pour over apples. Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting occasionally with the liquid.
Serve as garnish with roast turkey or as dessert topped with whipped cream.
Delicious.

title: dumplings for soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding enough flour to make mixture elastic.
Drop small teaspoons of mixture into soup. Check after 10 minutes.
Serve.
(Soup should be boiling when dropping dumpling mixture into it.)

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk together for 1 1/2 minutes. Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir and drop quickly on waxed paper and let dry.

title: creamy cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425° and mix all ingredients together.
Pour enough oil into a 9-inch iron skillet so that the bottom of the skillet is covered.
Place the oiled skillet in the oven until it is hot enough to sizzle (test by sprinkling a small amount of cornmeal in skillet).
Pour batter into heated skillet and bake for 15 to 25 minutes, depending on the oven.
Test center of cornbread with a toothpick to see if it is done.

title: lemon butter fruit cake
directions: Cream together light brown sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour, baking powder, pecans, red cherries, green cherries and pineapple.
Mix all together, then add lemon extract and orange juice.
(Keep stirring.)
Beat the 6 egg whites until foamy.
Fold in last; stir real good.
Bake in angel food pan; flour and grease cake pan.
Put batter in pan and let set overnight.
Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours over a pan of water.

title: chicken pamela
directions: Wash and place chicken flat in a baking dish (pre-sprayed with Pam cooking spray).
Layer the chicken with the pre-cut green pepper, red pepper, onion and tomato. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter and pour in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle over butter, one at a time, graham crackers, coconut, chocolate and butterscotch chips and nuts.
Pour milk over all.
Bake in 350° oven for not more than 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen squares.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and slice into 3/8-inch slices.
Salt and let slices drain on paper towels 30 minutes.
Pat dry.
Beat egg with 2 tablespoons water.
Dip eggplant first into egg mixture and then into bread crumbs.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Stir into vegetable mixture. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: tuna vegetable salad
directions: Bring water, peas, carrots, onions, salt and pepper to a full boil; stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Cover and chill.
Gently stir in tuna, pickle, mayonnaise and milk just before serving.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potatoes baked in oranges
directions: Cut the tops
off
the	oranges and with a spoon scrape out all the pulp.
Wash
the
sweet potatoes and boil in water until soft.
Drain
and
peel
them.
Mash
them	well
with a potato masher.
Add
cream
and butter, a little grated orange peel, salt, a
little
orange juice and 2 tablespoons of sugar and heat until
fluffy.
Fill
the
orange
cups with this and bake until lightly browned on top.

title: lazy man pickles
directions: Pack cucumber, onions and peppers tightly into jar.
Bring sugar, vinegar, canning salt, celery salt, mustard seed, alum and dill seed to boil and pour over pickle mixture.
Cool, then put in refrigerator, covered.
Will keep up to 1 year in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, vinegar and water.
Bring to boil and let cool.
Mix other ingredients and add to water mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Drain off juice; serve.
This can be prepared in advance.
Keeps fresh in refrigerator for weeks.

title: easy tomato-bean soup(fat free)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: quickie biscuits
directions: Add enough milk or water to flour and mayonnaise to make a thick batter.
Cook in a greased muffin pan at 400° or 450° until done.
Tastes great with butter and jelly.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and flour in skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, salt and pepper.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Place 2/3 of mixture in bottom of baked pie shell, called "crumbs".
In a saucepan, combine cornstarch, 1/4 teaspoon salt, egg yolks, vanilla, sugar, milk, butter and peanut butter.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over crumbs.
Beat together 3 egg whites, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 3 tablespoons sugar until stiff. Pour over pie.
Sprinkle on rest of crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chili wraps
directions: Saute onion in oil in large skillet.
Add beef. Cook until beef is brown or until done.
Season with peppers, hot sauce, chili powder, oregano, ketchup and garlic powder.
Place 1/8 of mixture in center of tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Fold over top and bottom edges.
Fold one side over filling, then other side.
Heat oil in skillet 1/2-inch high.
Fry tortillas folded-side down first.
Turn.
Brown other side.
Drain and serve.
Good served with rice.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk.
Blend well and chill.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Bake for 8 minutes.
(Don't let cookies brown; this will make them crisp.)

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie pan (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cook beef and onion.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat Bisquick milk and eggs about 1 minute.
Pour over hamburger.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer a few minutes.
Cool.
Pour over pickles and onions.
Refrigerate. Ready to eat in 7 days.

title: quick parmesan chicken
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Spoon over chicken that has been placed in a baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: luscious chicken pot pie(easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 365 degrees. Fit bottom pastry into a 10-inch pie plate. In a large bowl, combine chicken, soup and vegetables. Mix well, pour into crust. Cover with top pastry. Seal edges and cut steam vents in top. Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes, until crust is golden brown.

title: mexican burrito pie
directions: Mix together in a 9-inch pie plate to form pie shell and set aside.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Cool a little.
Add cranberries, fruit, celery and nuts.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Spread toasted nuts in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts.
Sprinkle coconut on top of cake batter and set aside.
Cream together cream cheese and margarine.
Add sugar and mix until creamy; spoon cheese mixture over batter and bake 1 hour.

title: swedish fruit soup
directions: Combine ingredients in a large kettle and bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often, until fruit is done.
Add more water, if necessary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: icebox cake
directions: Bake the cake as directed and while it is hot, pour the pineapple with juice over the
cake
and
cool
it.
Then
mix instant pudding and pour over the cool cake.
Let set a little while.
Then mix cream cheese
with
Cool Whip and spread over the cake.
It may be topped
with
chopped pecans if you wish. This cake is very good.

title: bacon rolls
directions: Mix sugars and ketchup in a saucepan and cook on low for 10 minutes. Cut bacon in thirds and cut water chestnuts in half. Wrap bacon around chestnuts, hold in place with a toothpick. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes on a cookie sheet. Remove from oven and cover with sauce, return to oven for 15-20 more minutes.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: In large saucepan, saute shrimp in butter until pink.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic and cook until tender.
Add milk and heat.
Blend in next 5 ingredients; heat and stir often.
Serve with garnish of additional shredded cheese.

title: peanut butter ice cream sundae pie
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter in a bowl until blended and smooth.
Spread
in
crust.
Freeze
at
least 3 hours or overnight.	Just
before
serving,	top
pie
with	the sliced banana, whipped cream, chocolate topping, nuts and a maraschino cherry.
Serves 8.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Separate 1 egg; reserve white in small bowl.
In large bowl, lightly beat two remaining eggs and one egg yolk; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Beat reserved egg white until stiff. Carefully fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour carefully into unbaked 10-inch pie shell.
Put tinfoil collar around crust edge to prevent burning.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove foil collar approximately 15 minutes before pie is done.
Cool and serve with real whipped cream.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt shortening; brown onion and meat.
Add celery, tomatoes and other seasonings.
Stir mixture.
Sprinkle rice over top.
Do not stir after adding rice.
Cover and cook on low for 30 minutes in heavy Dutch oven.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.

title: company best casserole
directions: Brown beef in heavy skillet until all red disappears.
Add onion, tomatoes, catsup, steak sauce, green pepper and parsley. Simmer 30 minutes.
Combine cooked macaroni and beef mixture; pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Season to taste.
Gently spoon mushroom soup into mixture, mixing lightly from bottom.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: glazed carrots(serves 4)
directions: In a medium-size saucepan, combine the carrots, butter, brown sugar, water, salt and pepper.
Bring the water to a boil.
Then let it bubble steadily for about 20 minutes, or until the carrots are cooked through and all the liquid in the pan has evaporated to form a glaze on the carrots.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve at once.

title: easy cranberry sauce
directions: Mix well and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: turkish beef deluxe
directions: Mix beef, parsley, onions, peppers, chopped tomatoes, 3/4 can of tomato sauce and spices.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Arrange vegetable slices over the beef mixture.
Thin remaining tomato sauce with a little water and pour over vegetables. Sprinkle with more salt and pepper, if desired.
Bake in a 375° oven, covered, for 1/2 hour or until done.
Serve with rice.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Place all in bowl and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: seven day pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, put in a roasting pan and cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Drain, rinse and repeat this process for 4 days.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Make sauce out of remaining ingredients. Pour over cooked broccoli.
Sprinkle with paprika. Broil about 3 inches from heat until brown.

title: round steak and gravy
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces.
Salt, pepper and flour each piece of meat.
Drain off grease.
Slice onion and add to meat.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes until steak is tender. Can use other cream soups.

title: tomato soup mold
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; add to soup.
Reheat.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set.
May use as a dip or serve on lettuce.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef; drain excess fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Lay noodles out and spread meat on noodles.
Add cheeses and mushrooms.
Roll noodles up.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon remaining sauce over each roll and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onions in margarine until tender.
Cut broccoli into bite sized pieces.
Mix with rice, soup, and Cheese Whiz.
Add onions and margarine.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add all canned ingredients.
Cook on low until simmering.
Serve over Doritos.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: no-toss salad
directions: Prepare each ingredient as directed.
Blend sour cream and sugar together well.
Blend salad dressing and vinegar together well.
Layer each ingredient in serving bowl.
Top with dressings, drizzled in overlapping directions.
Do not toss!

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together; pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: "surprise" pasta dessert
directions: Cook noodles; drain and let cool.
Drain juice from fruit into a pan.
Put fruit together into a container and refrigerate overnight.
Put eggs, sugar and flour into pan of fruit juice. Mix well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Pour over noodles.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, mix noodles, fruit and Cool Whip together.
Serve.
Scrumptious!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put in large bowl the peanut butter and marshmallow cream; leave it sit.
Combine in saucepan the powdered sugar, milk and cocoa.
Bring to boil.
Then pour it over peanut butter and marshmallow mixture.
Stir fast.
Put in square pan and cool.
Cut in squares.

title: breast of chicken a la parmigiana
directions: Pound breasts flat.
Dip in beaten eggs and milk; roll in bread crumbs.
Saute in butter.
Layer bottom of casserole with sauce, then breasts.
Cover each with a slice of Swiss cheese and Mozzarella.
Pour remaining sauce on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.
May be prepared ahead and baked just before serving.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken pieces in olive oil, season with garlic salt or regular salt.
Remove to a baking dish.
In frying pan add peppers, sliced, with more olive oil and saute.
Then add tomatoes, basil and mushrooms. Mix well.
Flavor with grated cheese and wine.
Mix well and pour over chicken in baking dish.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° in oven.
Serve with buttered noodles and a green salad.
Enjoy!

title: nonfat chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a 9-inch square pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl combine the dry ingredients and mix.
Whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup in a medium sized bowl.
Stir this into the dry ingredients until smooth, then pour the batter into the pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until the cake springs back when lightly touched.
Makes 16 servings.

title: mandelbread(mahn-dl bread*)
directions: Needs large jelly roll pan or 2 smaller pans, well-oiled.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles to desired tenderness; brown and drain hamburger, then mix with spaghetti sauce.
Layer the lasagna with noodles, sauce mix, then cheese until used up.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Layer in 8 x 12 pan or 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Slit and seed peppers.
Stuff peppers with half the cheese. Pinch peppers closed around the cheese.
Mix remaining cheese and sausage.
Add dry biscuit mix, 1/3 at a time, to make a stiff dough.
Knead several times.
Pinch off a bit of dough and pat into a flat pancake about 1/2-inch thick.
Place a stuffed pepper in the middle of each pancake and wrap completely with dough, making sure that all edges and ends are sealed.
Roll the dough covered pepper in your hands to mold into an egg shape.
Roll in Shake 'n Bake until coated.
Dip in beaten eggs and roll again in Shake 'n Bake.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes. (Center should be set.)
When done, it looks almost like a cake.

title: old black joe cake
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 350°.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Chill.
Just before serving, add dressing and Fritos; mix well.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well, shape into balls and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not store until cold.

title: company chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Top with soup and sour cream. Cover dish with foil; bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, garlic salt and chili powder over low heat until meat turns gray.
Drain fat.
Add soups and milk and picante sauce.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Pour over chips in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 to 15 or until cheese is melted and casserole bubbles. (May be heated in a microwave oven on Medium heat, if preferred.)

title: tomato juice wow
directions: Blend and refrigerate overnight.
Serve in frosted glasses. For more "wow" add vodka.

title: spring vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, syrup and water; boil until it threads.
Add peanuts; boil until brown.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla, stirring to mix well.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool, then break into pieces.

title: south hills' lynchburg lemonade
directions: Mix single shots in a glass and garnish with lemon slices and cherry or mix multiple shots in a punch bowl to serve many. Garnish with lemon slices
and cherry.
Serves single or many.

title: laced orange tea punch
directions: In a bowl, combine hot tea and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.
In punch bowl, combine tea, orange and lemon juices, orange liqueur and orange slices.
Chill until serving.
To serve, pour over ice in tall glass and garnish with orange slices.
Makes 5 cups.

title: isaacson family potato salad
directions: Dice bacon and fry until almost crisp, add chopped onion and saut until golden.
Melt margarine.
Drain bacon and onion into strainer over large measuring cup.
(Drippings and melted margarine should total 1 cup.)
Set aside.
Peel and grate potatoes. (Can use grating/shredding disc on food processor). Stir eggs, salt & evaporated milk into large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 X 13 baking dish (2-1/2 to 3 inches deep).
Place in preheated oven at 450 degrees for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350 degrees and bake until edges are crispy brown.
Cook about 1-1/2 hours. (Traditionally served with sour cream).

title: individual pizzas
directions: Lay flour tortillas on cookie sheets. Put a layer of spaghetti sauce on each tortilla.
Next put on a layer of your choice of toppings.
Finish with a layer of your choice of grated cheeses. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together over low heat both ingredients.
Pour into a square pan, greased.
Chill in refrigerator about 2 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: raspberry jam squares
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add egg yolks; blend well. Add flour slowly, mixing well.
Fold in nuts.
Put 1/2 mixture into greased 8-inch pan.
Spread jam on top.
Pat remaining mixture flat.
Cut into strips and place over jam.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: challah bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 1/2 of the flour into yeast.
Mix until smooth.
Add enough flour to handle easily.
Turn onto floured board; knead and let rise in greased bowl until doubled.
Punch down and separate into 3 equal parts.
Divide each of the three parts into three more parts.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and blend well the ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake an additional 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cover edge of crust with strips of foil after 30 minutes of baking to prevent excessive browning.

title: lamb on the grill
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over lamb and cover.
Refrigerate for about 6 hours, turning frequently if possible.
Prepare grill. Drain meat, reserving the marinade.
Grill lamb about 4 inches from coals, basting with marinade frequently.

title: *pineapple preserves("liko")
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan and cook until syrup thickens.
Pour into containers. Yields 2 jars.

title: grilled bacon, tomato and cheese sandwiches
directions: Toast bread and place on a cooking cooling rack.
Place rack over a pan to catch drippings.
On toast, place a slice of cheese, then thin slices of tomatoes.
Place strips of bacon over tomatoes. Grill until bacon is brown and crispy.
Bacon may be partly cooked first to remove some of the grease.

title: brownie mix
directions: Measure all ingredients into a large bowl and mix well.
An electric mixer may be used at low speed for 10 minutes.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Blend in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
I sometimes add chopped olives.
This is good on Ritz or Club crackers or as a chip dip.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cook cake and slice in half horizontally.
Whip all cream with sugar.
Layer as follows:
Cake, whip cream, cake, totally use the rest of the whip cream for the outside.
Serve the balance of the strawberries on the side.

title: green salad
directions: Using
a
large
glass
bowl,
layer
shredded lettuce, celery,
green pepper, diced onion and peas.
Add second layer of lettuce.
Cover
with Miracle Whip being careful to seal to edges. Sprinkle
top of dressing with sugar.
Add thick layer of Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with bits of crisp bacon.
Cover with plastic
wrap and chill for 24 hours.
Almost any fresh, chopped vegetable
can
be
added:
cauliflower,
broccoli, zucchini or mushrooms.

title: strawberries in white chocolate
directions: Rinse strawberries and dry thoroughly with paper towels.
Set berries aside.
Place white chocolate in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts.
Grasp strawberries by the stem
and dip into melted chocolate.
Place on a wire rack sprayed with vegetable cooking spray and chill until chocolate is firm.
Serve within 8 hours.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave margarine on High in glass bowl for 1 minute or until melted.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into buttered dish.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 1/3 pound.

title: eisenhower dish(a favorite of a president)
directions: In
a
greased
baking
dish, 8 x 8-inches and 2 inches deep, place
a layer of the rolled cracker crumbs and moisten well
with half of the cream sauce.
Next, a layer of cheese, then
a
layer of chopped pimentos topped with a layer of the grated eggs. Repeat these layers and again be sure the crumbs are
well moistened. Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients as listed in large mixing bowl.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan (fluted).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven door until done.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Cream butter with egg yolk.
Gradually add sugar and blend. Stir in chocolate and liquor.
Chill until firm to handle. Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Roll in coconut.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend first four ingredients together and then add peanuts. Chill for 1 hour.
This is used for dip for your favorite sliced apples.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans or a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Cream until fluffy the shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs; blend in chocolate.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir in alternately with buttermilk.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Form into balls and let set for 4 hours.

title: quick caramel ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Coat bottom and side of an ungreased 12-cup fluted tube pan with 2 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of nuts over bottom of pan.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining margarine.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift together flour, spices, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture. Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Coat with sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.
Self-rising flour does nicely also.

title: florentiner
directions: Combine nuts and fruit peel and flour; set aside.
In a 1-quart pan combine butter, milk and honey.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil until mixture reaches 240° on a candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Remove; stir in nut mixture. Drop 1 tablespoon at least 3 inches apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Spread into 2-inch circles.
Do no more than 8 or 9 at a time.
Bake at 350°.
Remove from oven and shape immediately into 3-inch rounds, by dipping a 3-inch cookie cutter into water and place around a hot cookie.
Let stand 1 minute; remove carefully with spatula to waxed paper.
Cool completely.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix 1 teaspoon cinnamon and the sugar.
Roll each biscuit in mixture.
Put pieces a well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix melted butter with remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture and pour over all.
Bake according to temperature and time on biscuit package.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash.
Add all ingredients, except the crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle layer of crumbs in shallow casserole dish. Spoon squash mixture over crumbs.
Cover with additional crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix the above ingredients until well blended; pat into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Put in refrigerator while mixing the Cheese Filling.
(I used a small food processor for the cookies and sugar and used potato masher to press down crumbs.)

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain and set aside.
Cook broccoli in 4 cups boiling water 2 minutes; remove and cool.
Add carrots to boiling water and cook 1 1/2 minutes; remove and cool. Saute pepper strips in oil until tender-crisp.
Add zucchini and garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add carrots, broccoli, pasta and seasonings.
Add butter and toss to coat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes about 12 cups or 8 servings.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Put in top of double boiler; beat until blended.
Place over boiling water.
Cook and beat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Heat in heavy pot and braise the meat until evenly browned on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Strain gravy and thicken to taste.
Slice when tender; serve with gravy.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: double cheese and mashed potato pie
directions: Combine and mix well first 6 ingredients.
Put in buttered 9-inch pie pan and sprinkle with bacon.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic salt, then dot with butter.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni salad(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix well and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: pork and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain grease.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is bubbly.

title: apricot pineapple salad
directions: Mix the pineapple and jello; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add cream cheese.
Stir to dissolve.
After it has cooled some, add apricot baby food, Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Remove unpopped kernels.
Bring the oleo, Karo and brown sugar to full boil, stirring constantly, and simmer for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon of soda and 1 teaspoon of vanilla flavoring.
Mix well and pour evenly over popped corn. Coat well and spread in cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 250°; pour out on waxed paper.

title: mushroom caps
directions: Take stems out of mushrooms and chop finely.
Chop shallots and garlic finely.
Mix with stems.
Place small cubes of cheese in mushroom cap.
Stuff caps with stems, shallots and garlic.
Put butter over caps and broil until mushrooms are soft.

title: hot sausage bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 12-15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Serve hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Thaw crawfish or shrimp if frozen.
In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, cook onions, celery, green pepper and garlic, covered, in oil, margarine or butter about 10 minutes, stirring until melted.
Stir in cornstarch.
Stir in crawfish or shrimp, water, tomato sauce, salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until crawfish are tender or shrimp turn pink.
Serve with hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: t.v. mix
directions: Mix butter or margarine, oil, garlic powder, savory salt and Worcestershire sauce together.
Put cereal, pretzel sticks and nuts into a very large roasting pan.
Pour oil mixture over cereal mixture and bake in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Strain them.
Beat eggs well. Mix milk, sugar and eggs into potatoes.
Beat well or stir thoroughly.
Mix in pineapples.
Add allspice.
Mix in raisins, cherries, pecans and marshmallows.
Pour into a large baking dish and sprinkle with coconut.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a mixing bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse meal. Add cheese and milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 8 to 10 times. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter. Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 1 dozen biscuits.

title: soda cracker chocolate candy
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan (jelly roll pan works great) with foil and coat with nonstick cooking spray.
Place crackers in rows on foil.
In a saucepan, melt butter; add the brown sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers; spread until completely covered.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes (crackers will float).
Remove from oven.
Turn oven off.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and walnuts over crackers.
Return to oven until chocolate is melted, about 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Using a greased spatula, press walnuts into chocolate.
Cut into cracker size squares while warm.
Cool completely.
Remove candy from foil. Great gift idea!

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and onion together slowly.
Add the flour, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Turn heat off.
Taste.
It must be quite sour.
Mix the celery and green pepper, then the sliced, cooled potatoes.
Add to the bacon mixture.
Warm slowly, so it won't burn.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; save stems for use in soups or sauces.
Brush mushroom caps with oil and place in buttered baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine crabmeat, egg, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Fill caps with mixture. Combine remaining bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over crab mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in a saucepan.
Saute garlic for 1 minute.
Add clam juice, wine, thyme and pepper to garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add clams and parsley and simmer until heated thoroughly.
Cook linguine according to package directions and drain.

title: spicy party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cereal, peanuts, pretzels and sesame seeds.
In a saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over the cereal mixture and stir to coat. Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes or until golden brown, stirring once.
Cool completely. Store in airtight container.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until bubbling. Garnish with sage.
Extra Cheddar added to soup if desired.

title: ladle-it-on lasagna
directions: Cook onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, garlic, basil and oregano. Simmer, uncovered, for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the Romano cheese.
Spoon hot pasta on plate.
Top with tomato sauce, 1/4 Ricotta cheese and 1 1/2 tablespoons Mozzarella.

title: soup salad
directions: Heat soup, water and cream cheese.
(Don't melt all of the cheese, let some be in lumps.)
Soak gelatin in cold water, then dissolve in hot mixture. Add salt and cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, add mayonnaise and vegetables.
Congeal.

title: quick broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain and put into casserole dish with the cream of mushroom soup.
Add stuffing mix. Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain, leaving a little oil in the pan.
Add onions and garlic.
Stir in sauce, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until thick; about 25 minutes.
Cook the macaroni and drain.
Prepare a 3-quart greased casserole by filling it with layers of macaroni, beef mixture and cheeses.
Top with Mozzarella.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Break bread into pieces and layer part into 9 x 13-inch pan. Put part of cheese over bread, all of ham over cheese and then rest of bread on top.
Put rest of cheese over all.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over all.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour or more.
Sprinkle more grated cheese and bake for 5 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients after browning beef.
Bring to a boil and pour over any type of noodles.

title: black bean sauce(for stuffed zucchini)
directions: Heat garlic and ginger in oil until aromatic, approximately 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove.
Add rinsed black beans and stir for 1 minute.
Add the oyster sauce, shoyu sauce, sugar and chicken broth.
Add salt and aji to taste.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with a little broth and water.
Add chopped green onions.
Pour over stuffed zucchini and serve.

title: chocolate mint squares
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with next 3 ingredients (mixed).
Melt together chocolate chips and butter.
Glaze the squares with this mixture.
Put in refrigerator to set the glaze.

title: candy apple salad
directions: Combine whipped topping and pineapple in a bowl.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Quarter slices.
Cut Snickers bars into small cubes.
Chop nuts.
Fold apples, candy and nuts into Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: In a 5-quart pot, saute first 4 ingredients, stirring constantly until slightly softened, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour the chicken stock into pot to cover vegetables.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat, throw in bay leaves, parsley and pepper.
Cover and simmer for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours until vegetables are very soft. Pour in milk.
The vegetables can be left whole, or you can mash just as is in the pot, or blend the soup in a blender.
Mashing part of the vegetables is my choice.
Serve with a thick piece of French bread; delicious and very filling.
Serves 6.

title: waffles
directions: Set mixer at high speed.
Beat whole eggs one minute, add the milk and beat for one minute longer.
Add the sifted dry ingredients to this mixture and beat one minute longer.
Add the melted shortening and beat 15 seconds or until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Makes 6 waffles.

title: creamy cabbage soup(microwave)
directions: Wash, dry and pierce potatoes. Cook in microwave for 7 minutes. Remove from oven and set aside.
Place onions and butter in 4-cup glass measuring cup. Cover tightly with microwave plastic wrap. Cook for
3 minutes and remove from oven.
Uncover and stir in cabbage. Cover and cook for 4 minutes.
Peel and cut potatoes into chunks.
Place in work bowl of food processor.
Add cabbage and broth to potatoes.
Process until well combined, but not completely smooth.
Pour mixture into bowl and stir in cream. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: quick bread or rolls(cinnamon)
directions: Mix milk, sugar, margarine and salt together; cool to lukewarm.
Add the yeast and eggs.
Add flour and mix well. Place in well-greased large bowl and let rise until double in size.
Cover with wet, warm cloth while rising.
Punch down and turn out on well floured board.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Divide in half.
Roll out about 1-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter for rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Put vanilla in first hole, vinegar in second hole and oil in the third hole.
Pour water over all ingredients. Mix with fork.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: strawberry pretzel jello salad
directions: Crush pretzels, using a rolling pin (not too fine).
Mix crushed pretzels, 3 tablespoons of sugar and melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: carnation meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Place in loaf dish.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add applesauce and raspberries.
Chill and serve.
May be topped with whipped cream.

title: baked alaska
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg to foamy stage in large bowl with beaters.
Add vanilla and cream of tartar; beat to soft peaks. Add sugar gradually.
Cover cake with meringue to seal sides.
Cook until tan.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Mix together well the sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and hit bottom of pie pan on counter so pie will fall.
Cool completely.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Mix juices and place in bottom of percolator.
Place rest of ingredients in top basket.
Let perk through one cycle and remove basket.
Serve hot.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Near end of cooking time, heat 1/2 stick margarine and about 1 1/2 cups brown sugar plus 3 to 4 tablespoons milk until margarine is melted.
Pour mixture over the cake as soon as it is removed from the oven.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Broil until sugar bubbles.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Use an 8 x 14 x 2-inch glass baking dish.

title: rose's coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar; add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to bowl alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.

title: quick and easy macaroons
directions: Mix coconut, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 1-inch apart, onto well-greased cookie sheets, pressing down ends of coconut with back of spoon.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Top with almonds or maraschino cherries, if desired.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a dish; add sliced eggs.
Mix chicken broth and celery soup; pour over chicken.
Melt margarine.
Add and mix flour and milk; pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° until crust browns.
Batter will form crust.

title: black-eyed peas with rich casserole
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix chicken with onion, cheese, Ro-Tel, garlic salt and chili powder.
Soften tortillas in broth.
Layer 6 to 8 tortillas in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 of mixture and repeat.
Top with cans of soup.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat potatoes, butter, milk, eggs and flavoring well.
Divide into pie shells and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients and then add Italian dressing to taste.
Serve with dippable chips like Fritos or Scoops.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs at high speed to combine. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick and lemon color.
Beating constantly, pour in oil.
With mixer at low speed, blend in sifted dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with dry ingredients, beating until smooth after each addition. Stir in walnuts.
Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done when tested. Cool on rack completely before removing from pan.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and bake in 4 layers for 15 or 20 minutes.
(I had difficulty in removing the cake from the pans because of them being so moist.
The best solution I've found to this problem is to put spray cooking oil in the bottom and on the sides of the pans and then put a piece of waxed paper in the bottom.)

title: dump cake
directions: In bottom of a glass pan put crushed pineapple.
Smear blueberry pie filling on top.
Sift 1 box of cake mix on top. Melt 1 stick of butter; pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: mexican fiesta party dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass pan, layer the ingredients in order listed with the refried beans on the bottom and the tomatoes on top.
Chill.
Serve with chips and salsa or you can sprinkle the salsa on top and serve with chips.
Can be made a day ahead.
Keep refrigerated.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine and place in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and remaining 2 eggs and pour on top of first mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool completely before cutting.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Slowly add macaroni and salt to boiling water.
Cook, stirring occasionally until tender.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again.
Drain liquid from the pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup of the liquid.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, pineapple, oranges, grapes, celery, marshmallows and apples in small bowl.
Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, reserved pineapple juice and lemon until smooth.
Toss macaroni mixture with sour cream mixture.
Chill well.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cook in greased loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
In pan, saute garlic, zucchini and pepper in oil.
Heat tomatoes with liquid, basil, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat through and toss over fettucini; top with fresh grated Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: roasted potatoes parmesan
directions: Pierce each potato in several places with a fork. Arrange in a single layer in a shallow pan. Bake in a 375° oven until tender (about 1 hour).
Let cool slightly.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Bake pastry shell at 350° for 5 minutes. Combine eggs and remaining ingredients in a medium bowl and stir well. Spoon egg mixture evenly into pastry. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet until crumbly.
Drain.
Add salt, taco mix, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chiles.
Blend well. Bring to boil,
reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered 10 minutes.
In small bowl, combine
Ricotta
cheese
and eggs.
In 13 x 9-inch baking
dish, spread
half
ground
beef.
Top
with half each tortillas, Ricotta mixture and
Jack
cheese.
Repeat
layers, ending with Jack cheese.
Bake, uncovered
at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin cobbler
directions: Mix cake mix and margarine until crumbly.
Set aside.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix pumpkin, sugars, eggs, spices, salt and evaporated milk and pour into baking dish.
Put cake mixture on top.
Top with nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: preserving children
directions: Mix the children with the dogs and cats; empty into the field, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle field with flowers.
Pour the creek gently over pebbles.
Cover all with deep blue sky and bake in the hot sun.
When children are well browned, they may be removed; put in bathtub with 1 bar of soap.
Put to bed with God's love!
It really works!

title: company chicken bake
directions: *Use regular rice.
If Minute rice is used, it becomes mushy.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush up Oreos until they look like dirt; put in bowl.
Melt butter and add to cookies.
Set aside.

title: sweet ripe cukes
directions: Peel cukes.
Cut in 2 lengthwise.
Scrape out seeds with spoon. Salt and let stand overnight.

title: orange juice spritzer
directions: In a large, nonmetal pitcher, combine orange juice concentrate, water and lemon juice.
Just before serving, slowly add carbonated beverage; stir gently to blend.
Serve over ice in glasses.
Garnish with orange and lime slices.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together. Chill 4 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: kinako doughnuts
directions: Preheat oil for deep frying.
In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Shape into small balls with hand or spoon.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve warm, if desired.

title: blender chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs in blender 20 seconds. Mix sugar and cocoa in a bowl. Add sugar mixture to eggs in a blender with milk, vanilla and margarine.
Blend until well mixed. Pour into pie shell. Bake 40 to 50 minutes until pie is done. Pie will rise high and fall somewhat when cool.

title: crispy oven-fried okra
directions: Wash okra; trim ends and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine corn meal, salt and pepper in a medium bowl; stir and set aside. Combine buttermilk and egg in a large bowl; stir in okra.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Dredge okra in corn meal.
Place okra on a baking sheet coated with Pam.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes, or until crisp. Stir often.
Makes 12 servings

title: oven-fried chicken with biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt oleo in baking pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Mix baking mix, salt, paprika and pepper; coat chicken pieces.
Place chicken pieces, skin side down, in pan. Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes.
Insert clove in each peach half. Prepare biscuits as directed on package of Bisquick baking mix. Turn chicken, pushing pieces to side of pan.
Spoon excess fat from pan.
Place biscuits in single layer next to chicken. Arrange peach halves on chicken.
Bake until biscuits are light brown and chicken is done, about 15 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken-wing singapore
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, mustard and garlic powder in flat pan.
Put in the wings and turn until coated.
Marinate for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Bake in same pan at 375° for 1 hour. Baste while cooking.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Bring to a boil pineapple and sugar.
Add jello and cream cheese.
Let cool.
Add apples, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into a greased mold and chill.
When you start to serve, put cherries on top.

title: pineapple chicken stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry chicken chunks.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Add additional pineapple juice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Combine juice, teriyaki sauce, cornstarch and brown sugar; set aside.

title: almond cooler
directions: Pour the boiling water over tea bags.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags; discard.
Chill tea at least 2 hours.
At serving time, spoon sherbet into 4 chilled glasses; pour in chilled tea. Stir just until blended.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) servings.

title: snow on the mountain
directions: Spray cookie sheet.
On cookie sheet, place the hot dogs or sausages (8).
In a bowl, combine the mashed potatoes that have been prepared according to directions.
Mix in onion, sour cream, salt and pepper until well mixed.
Divide up mixture evenly on hot dogs on cookie sheet; dollop mixture on top of each hot dog.
Make a hollow in potatoes with back of spoon.
Fill opening with cheese. Bake until hot dogs are cooked, about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Brown chuck and onions together.
Drain grease.
Put meat and onion in bottom of crockpot.
Layer with potatoes, corn, beans and then spread soup all over.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Cook 7-9 hours on low.
Feeds 4-6.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Spread chicken and vegetables evenly in prepared dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in small mixing bowl.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine baking mix, milk and butter in separate bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Pour flour mixture over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat to a boil.
Stir chicken pieces.
Reduce heat to a simmer and cook for one hour, stirring chicken occasionally.
Remove chicken and thicken sauce with a mixture of cornstarch and water.
Serve with rice and a salad.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup of cold water.
Stir in drained oranges and pineapple.
Pour into a long glass bowl; refrigerate until completely set.
Ice with Cool Whip; top lightly with cheese.

title: fried mullet southern style(6 servings)
directions: Clean and wash the fish.
Dry on clean towel.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dip into slightly beaten egg.
Roll in corn meal.
Fry in deep fat.
Drain on crushed paper.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Peel and quarter onion.
Cut stem from eggplant; cut in half lengthwise and put skin side up in ungreased roasting pan with lid, along with peppers and onion.
Roast, uncovered, at 375° for 17 minutes.
Turn onion and peppers and roast 17 minutes more.
Remove from oven; cover and let sit until cool.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix oil and milk, add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring only until mixed.
Bake in greased 9 inch pan for 12-15 minutes.
Cut in half while warm and stack layers with strawberries between and on top.
May cut in squares and make individual servings.
Oven temperature 450 degrees.

title: pop wessons' caramel nut candy
directions: *I do not use Karo syrup.
I use Blackburn or Pride of Dixie.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and use favorite "sauce or dressing." Use Fruit fresh on fruit.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook ground beef in a large saucepan until browned.
Drain. Stir in tomatoes (including juice), chopped onion, sliced carrots, chopped celery, barley, catsup, bouillon, season salt, crushed basil and water.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for one hour.
Serves 6.

title: western beef sandwiches
directions: For topping, melt butter in medium sized saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and is smooth.
Add onion and beef.

title: summertime pasta salad
directions: Can add any amount: chopped onion, green pepper, cheese, pepperoni, boiled eggs.

title: pecan drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with salt; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, margarine, sugar, cream and vanilla until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture until well combined.
Stir in nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden.
Remove to wire rack; cool.

title: chewy caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with milk in double boiler over low heat.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup, well and place in a dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spoon soup over meat loaf. Bake for 1 hour at 400° or until done.

title: egg custer
directions: Mix together eggs (beaten), sugar, nutmeg, salt and vanilla. Set aside.
Heat milk; don't boil.
When milk is hot, add first mixture.
Bake at 400° about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: speedy spinach lasagna
directions: Heat
first
ingredients,
stirring
until
blended. Remove from
heat.
Beat
eggs in a large bowl and add cheese, spinach, salt and 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover
with
a
little
sauce.
Layer
noodles, cheese, spinach, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes.
Place tomatoes on top (do not stir).
Refrigerate.
This recipe is from my aunt, Mable Odom.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Add bread crumbs to milk and let stand a few minutes.
Mix with ground beef, egg, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Shape into a loaf and place into a baking dish or pan.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Mix all ingredients until well blended. Chill.

title: bishop casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add browned meat.
Dissolve cheese (room temperature) and mix with mushroom soup.
Add soup, cheese and corn to meat; put in dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or 1 hour at 300°.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix together tomato sauce, lemon juice, onion, cilantro and tomatoes.
Add salt, if desired.

title: jiffy clam puffs*
directions: Blend ingredients and pile on rounds of bread.
Broil until brown and puffy.
Serve piping hot.

title: low-fat "fried" chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts.
Rinse chicken and pat dry. Finely crush cornflakes (1 cup).
Stir together cornflake crumbs, sage, marjoram or basil.
Set aside.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brush chicken with milk.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture, patting to coat each side evenly.
Place chicken, meat side up, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no cook fondant
directions: Blend margarine, Karo syrup, salt and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Add sifted powdered sugar.
Mix first with spoon and then with hands, kneading in dry ingredients.
Makes 1 1/3 pounds.
Can be made into mints or put in dates.
Must be refrigerated.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Combine honey, oil, mustard, curry powder and salt in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is done, basting with honey mixture every 15 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *I use the water I boil the chicken breasts in.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except soup and water, and form into balls.
Combine soup and water.
Drop meatballs into mixture and cook over low heat, covered, for about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: steak fiesta
directions: Cook onions in margarine in medium saucepan until tender.
Add tomatoes, 1/4 cup steak sauce and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; stir in parsley.
Broil steaks or grill until desired doneness.
Brush with remaining steak sauce.
Serve with vegetable mixture.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients; mix well.
Add 1 egg and mix.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine butter, water and chocolate.
Bring to a boil.
Add 2 eggs, sour cream, baking soda, salt, flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Spoon cheese mixture over chocolate batter.
Cut through with knife several times for marbled effect. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crust for quiche and tarts
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese.
Add cream.
Mix flour and salt. Add to butter mixture and mix all together.
Roll out to fit pans.

title: eggnog(non-alcoholic)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend on low speed for 20 seconds.
Serve cold with a little whipped cream on top, if desired.
Yields one portion.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take meat from the bones.
Put on the bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soup and milk.
Pour this over chicken.
Melt butter/margarine.
Put over the mixture in the dish.
Sprinkle poppy seeds over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: banana split pie
directions: Note:
One-fourth pie equals 1 bread, 1 fruit and 1 milk. Contains 50 calories.

title: edna brown slush punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil or until sugar is dissolved. While hot (not boiling), add Jell-O.
Cool.
Add juices, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add 1 gallon water and almond extract.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes covered, then 10 minutes without cover until lightly brown.

title: turkey hash
directions: In large cooking pot, heat oil.
Add onion, bell pepper and sage.
Saute about 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt (if desired) and black pepper.
Cook 2 additional minutes.
Stir in cooked turkey, potatoes and broth; mix well.
Reduce heat to low; cook uncovered about 10 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to instructions.
Crumble bread into a large bowl.
Add chopped peppers, onion and tomato.
Add crumbled, cooked bacon.
Mix well with mayo.

title: frosted sugar cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar and margarine at medium speed with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well. Combine 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt, stirring well. Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well. Cover and chill 2 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Leave rest in refrigerator.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon flour on work area surface. Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch cutter. Place cookies on sheet with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Combine powdered sugar and water.
Spread on cookies.

title: dilled cauliflower salad
directions: Bring 1/2 inch of water to a boil in a saucepan; add chopped cauliflower and frozen peas.
Bring to a boil for 4 minutes.
Run cold water over drained vegetables.
Drain well.
Add the other ingredients and enough mayonnaise to cover.
Serve cold.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Fill greased loaf pans (medium size) 1/2 full.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and water in a medium saucepan.
Heat for 4 to 5 minutes over low heat or until butter melts.
Add chocolate pieces; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a large mixer bowl; cool for 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs one at a time at high speed.
Gradually beat flour, baking soda and salt into chocolate mixture at low speed.
Cover and chill dough for 1 hour.

title: divinity
directions: Cook 3 cups sugar, 3/4 cup water and corn syrup until fairly hard ball when tested (260°).
Remove from heat and pour slowly over egg whites.
At this time, starting cooking 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Cook until very hard ball (300°).
Add to first mixture and beat.
Add vanilla and nuts or cherries.
Drop on wax paper with teaspoon.
Makes about 75 drops.

title: cheese appetizers
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour and pepper. Chill and roll into 3/4-inch balls. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Place in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 370° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: california chicken risotto
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and red pepper; set aside.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic. Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add chicken; cook and stir until no longer pink.
Add rice.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add broth to skillet; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in bell pepper.
Remove from heat.
Let stand covered until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted and creamy.
Stir in tomato and basil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute gently until just golden, about 1 minute.
Do not let garlic brown.
Add clams and their liquid, red pepper, oregano and lemon juice.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes over low heat.
Add parsley and cook 1 minute.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Boil 2 cups mashed berries, sugar and tapioca.
Put 2 cups of fresh berries in baked pie shell.
Cover with boiled mixture.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: soda cracker candy(mock heath bar)
directions: Line the cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
(Cookie sheet should have an edge.)
Smear some of the butter around on the aluminum. Don't use the whole stick, but cover the aluminum very well.
Line the cookie sheet with crackers.
Make sure they are all touching. In a saucepan, boil the sugar and all of the rest of the butter over medium heat for 5 minutes or until it reaches the crack stage. (Stir constantly.)
Pour over crackers and spread.
Put in preheated oven (350°) for 10 minutes.
Remove carefully so the spread doesn't move off the crackers.
Sprinkle chips over top. Set for 3 minutes.
Spread with a spatula.
Chill.
Cut and serve.

title: chicken mozzarella and herb butter
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix berries, egg and oil.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, combine apples, sweetened condensed milk and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, cut 1/2 cup margarine into 1 cup biscuit mix until crumbly.
Stir in apple mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup biscuit mix and sugar.
Cut in remaining 2 tablespoons margarine until crumbly; add nuts.
Sprinkle evenly over apple mixture.
Bake one hour or until golden.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo in saucepan.
Mix together, stirring on medium heat, until boiling.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix and drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper and let cool.

title: salmon party meal
directions: Drain and flake salmon.

Remove skin and bones. Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke. Mix thoroughly. Chill several hours. Combine pecans and parsley. Shape into a ball and roll in nut and parsley mixture. Garnish with cheery cherry tomatoes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Bread the cutlets in Parmesan and bread crumbs, then fry in a little butter and garlic.
Remove when done and set aside.
Add Marsala wine, chicken broth and sliced mushrooms to butter and garlic mixture.
Cook until mushrooms are soft, then add the chicken cutlets and cook for another 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine chicken, salt, grapes, almonds, mayonnaise and cantalope.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Fill cantalope shells with chicken mixture.
Serves 6.

title: quick guacamole
directions: In a bowl, mash the avocado.
Stir in cottage cheese and picante or salsa sauce.
Add jalapeno, if desired.

title: cheese cake
directions: Place graham cracker crust in a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Mix all other ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Pour into pan. Bake in 325° oven for one hour.
Turn oven off and leave the cheese cake in the oven for two more hours.
Do not open oven. This is absolutely delicious!

title: almond apple wheat stuffing
directions: Saute apples, almonds, onion and celery in butter for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Stir in cinnamon, poultry seasoning and salt. Toss together bread cubes and raisins. Add apple mixture.
Stir egg in 1/3 cup apple cider. Toss into bread mixture. Add remaining apple cider if a moister stuffing is desired.
This will stuff a 15 to 20 pound turkey or 2 large roasting chickens.
Spoon any remaining stuffing into a lightly greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake, covered.
Makes 10 cups.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies until fine; set aside.
In large bowl, add milk to pudding mix.
Mix well.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
In bowl or flower pot, layer crumbs and pudding mixture, starting and finishing with crumbs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in butter.
Add mushroom soup and garlic cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over cooked and drained broccoli.
Add buttered bread crumbs on top and cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix pumpkin, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix until blended. Add oil, nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix together until well blended.
Pour mixture into greased tube pan and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
(Only while cake is warm, cover with glaze of powdered sugar mixed with enough orange juice to thin consistency).

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Dribble melted margarine on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts and mix with mayo and cheese.
Cook until bubbly.
Place in Pyrex dish; cover with lid.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes or until brown around edges.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: pineapple-chicken lo mein
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Set pineapple aside. In a large skillet over medium heat, cook the chicken, garlic and ginger in 2 tbsp oil for 6 minutes.
