Add the carrots, green pepper and pineapple.
Cover and cook for 2-3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender and chicken juices run clear.
Stir in spaghetti and onions.
In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch, soy sauce, reserved pineapple juice and remaining oil until smooth.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Bring to a boil, cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.

title: cream cheese peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped topping. Pour into pie crust.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy good pierogi
directions: Filling:
Boil potatoes until tender.
Add Cheez Whiz and mash with potato masher.
Mix first 4 ingredients for dough and roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter or glass to make desired size circles.
Fill circle with approximately 1 1/2 teaspoons filling; fold in half and fork on both sides.
Enough for about 35.
Boil in water until they float, then fry in butter and onions until lightly browned on each side.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: beer joint chili
directions: Fry
tallow,
then add onions and garlic.
Add meat and cook in its own juice until almost done.
Stir in small bottle of Gebhardt
chili powder or less.
Add black pepper and salt to taste,
then
add
Spanish-style
tomato
sauce and water. Simmer 1/2 hour or less, then eat.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Heat water and sugar until sugar melts. Cut shortening in flour. Add milk and roll out dough on a floured board. Shape into a large rectangle. Sprinkle apples and cinnamon evenly over dough. Roll up like a jelly roll. Slice dough into about 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick. Place in a pan with melted butter. Pour sugar syrup around rolls. They absorb all the liquid. Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Bake cake mix in jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch) according to instructions on the box.
Cool thoroughly. Beat together cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread pudding mixture on cooled cake.
Sprinkle drained pineapple mixture on pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in shallow pan over low heat. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Add Chex and nuts.
Mix over low heat until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread out on absorbent paper towels to cool.
Makes 6 3/4 cups mix.

title: pork chop and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil in a large skillet, about 3 minutes on each side.
Remove to plate.
Add onion rings to skillet; saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; reserve.
Melt butter in a medium-size saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; cook 1 minute.
Add milk and broth slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat.

title: royal wine cooler
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart pitcher, place oranges and lime slices. Sprinkle with sugar.
Press fruit with back of spoon to release juice.
Add brandy and half of wine; chill 1 to 2 hours.
Stir in the remaining wine and club soda.
Serve over ice, garnished with orange and lime slices.

title: strawberry braid
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in granulated sugar, 1/2 cup milk, the butter, eggs, salt, whole wheat flour and 1 cup of all-purpose flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs well in large bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients, mixing well, but not enough to crush corn. Pour into rectangular, 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish.
Place dish in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set larger dish on oven rack.
Fill larger dish with 1-inch boiling water.
Bake 1 hour until pudding is set.

title: hot cranberry casserole
directions: In 2-quart buttered casserole, put apples and cranberries. Cover with lemon juice and sugar.
Top with margarine, oats, nuts and brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Boil water in saucepan, after boiling, add shrimp until pink, drain and set aside.
In large pan, melt butter, add scallions and cook until tender.
Add 1 1/2 tsp. Seafood Magic and blend. Slowly add heavy cream and asiago cheese.
Stir until well blended and starting to thicken.
Add shrimp.
Serve over any type pasta and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
(You can melt any white cheese that you like, however something with flavor is best.)

title: candy kisses
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into other batter.
Shape dough in balls with teaspoon.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove sheet from oven and insert one candy kiss in each cookie; press down firmly so cookie cracks.
Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: tropical summer punch
directions: Combine pineapple chunks, undrained, and orange juice and limeade concentrates in a punch bowl.
Add 2 orange juice cans water.
Pour in the ginger ale, cranberry juice and apple juice. Float frozen strawberries and lemon slices on top.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well.
Better if made the night before.

title: mama heidi's quick blackberry cobbler
directions: Pour berries into a bowl.
Pour half the sugar over the berries and stir.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put stick of margarine into cake pan. Set in oven to melt butter.
Mix flour, milk and sugar in mixing bowl. Dough should be same consistency as cake dough.
May have to add milk or flour to get to proper consistency.
Pour mixture into cake pan on top of melted butter. Pour fruit into batter.
Distribute evenly. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes or until brown. Check to make sure dough is baked all the way through.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ground beef, onion and garlic until brown and tender.
Drain well.
Stir in vegetables and seasonings. Bring to boil and boil gently, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in spaghetti.
Place half of mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.
(Freezes well.)

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Boil 1 minute in saucepan. Add peanut butter.
Add oats.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and chill until firm in refrigerator.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Boil carrots for about 5 minutes and drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours, turning bowl upside down and shaking to distribute marinade.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice. Stir to melt.
Chill until runny, then add pineapple and oranges. Chill.

title: b.b.q.  mini meat loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat egg in bowl.
Mix in beef, pork, 2/3 C. barbecue sauce, crumbs, parsley, onion, garlic, and salt.
Shape scant 3/4 C. mixture into 4 x 2 x 1 inch loaf, for total of 6. Place on jelly-roll pan.
Top each loaf with about 2 Tbsp. of remaining barbecue sauce.
Bake in 350 degree oven 30 minutes.
Let stand on pan 10 minutes.
Serve immediately or cool completely; refrigerate and serve cold.

title: strawberry chicken salad
directions: Toss romaine lettuce in large bowl with chicken, oranges and strawberries.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Serve with dressing. Serves 4.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and spread on a large platter. Layer with the lettuce, scallions, tomatoes and cheese.
Use your favorite tortilla chips for dipping.

title: russian refresher mix(an imitation russian tea - without the tea)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix well. Put in a 1-quart airtight container.
Label. Store in a cool, dry place. Use within 6 months.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups of Russian Refresher Mix.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain.
Combine noodles, soup, tuna, cheese, mayonnaise, milk and peas.
Mix well and put into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beat well.
Add vanilla and butter extract. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Store in airtight container.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Shape firmly into loaf.

title: no cholesterol cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake at 350°.
Check after 30 minutes.

title: arkansas apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and cut into 8 pieces each.
Roll out crescents and sprinkle liberally with cinnamon.
Roll 1 piece of apple in each crescent and place in 10 x 10 pan sprayed with Pam.
Melt butter and mix with sugar and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over the apple crescents.
Pour Mountain Dew over the top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put boiling water, vinegar and salt into a large pot.
Bring back to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Put cucumbers in pot and let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove cucumbers with a drip spoon. Pack cucumbers in 9-quart jars.
To the jars add the dill seed, garlic, 1/4 red hot pepper and alum.
Reheat liquid and then pour over cucumbers and seal jars.

title: pecan cake(good fruit cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks (one at a time).
Stir nutmeg into grape juice and add to mixture.
Fold in flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cube pineapple and cut cherries in halves.
Roll all fruit and nuts into extra flour. Add to cake mixture.
Cook in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Cook one more hour at 275°.
Let cool completely in pan before removing.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until vegetables are soft.
Add salt, picante sauce, seasonings and olives; simmer 5 minutes and set aside.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, dissolve sugar, shortening and salt in warm milk.
Beat in 1 egg.
Add 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add yeast mixture. Beat in, then add 1/2 of flour.
Continue working in the rest of the flour.
The dough will be sticky.
Grease the dough with some margarine and grease a large bowl.
Cover.
Let rise until double. Punch down.
Let rise again.
Roll out dough to 1/3 inch.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Let rise to double.
Fry in deep oil at 375° until brown.
Turn over.
Repeat on the other side.

title: frosted coffee
directions: Whirl the coffee and ice cream in a blender or food processor (may be blended in three batches, if necessary) until thick and frosty.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix together well.
Shape into meatballs using 1 tablespoon for each.

title: mamaw's blueberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let congeal.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and mix with enough buttermilk to make soft batter.
Fold in bacon bits.
Grease and preheat corn bread skillet.
Fill pan half full and cook over low heat on top of stove about 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown around the edges.
Turn with spatula and continue cooking until done.
Turn out on plate to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender.
Drain and save liquid.
Set vegetables aside.
In the same pot, saute onion in butter or margarine until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is desired consistency.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt and mix, then let it come to a little boil.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Add 1 teaspoon of baking soda.
Stir over popcorn.
Put in oven at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.
Double for larger family.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bottom with white bread (9 slices, no crust) that have been buttered on both sides.
Cover bread with thin sliced ham.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and chives.
Cover meat layer with thick sliced Swiss cheese.
Layer with bread again, same as before.

title: shrimp and egg balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except parsley.
Shape into 8 balls.
Roll in parsley.
Chill.
Serve with dressing on lettuce bed.

title: pepparkakor cookies
directions: Heat syrup with shortening and light brown sugar.
Cool. Combine egg, milk, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and baking soda.
Add flour.
Combine with syrup; knead dough.
Refrigerate.
Divide dough into 3 parts and roll thin.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: brownie melt-aways
directions: Prepare brownies as directed on package, except stir in coconut and nuts.
Bake.
Cool.

title: taco rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
I use 1 cup of rice to 2 cups water.

title: bean soup bread
directions: Combine yeast, water and Shredded Wheat biscuits.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Beat egg and bean soup with mixer.
Add to the yeast mixture.
Add sugar, molasses, salt and shortening.
Mix until smooth.
Beat in 2 cups of flour.
Add enough remaining flour to make soft ball.
Knead, adding more flour to make the dough smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; let rise 1 hour.
Punch down; let rise 1/2 hour longer.
Turn out on floured breadboard.
Let rest 10 minutes after dividing it into 3 loaves.
Let rise until dough is almost level with pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato crisps
directions: Slice potatoes very thinly and arrange 12 slices on a microwave-safe trivet or roasting rack. Microwave on High for 3 minutes (making sure slices do not burn). Continue to microwave on High for 1 minute, checking after 30 seconds.
Sweet potato crisps will look dry and feel crisp.
Remove crisps to a large plate. Repeat with 12 more sweet potato slices until all slices are used. Sprinkle sweet potato crisps with confectioners sugar and apple pie spice.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: punkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, then mix 2 cups of flour and 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Cook until done.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Heat 3 pints of milk; add other ingredients and cook until slightly thickened.
When cooled (doesn't have to be cold, just not boiling), add 2 cans evaporated milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add enough whole milk in addition to the 3 pints to make a gallon.
Freeze in a hand type freezer.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Combine chicken, cottage cheese, olives, pimiento, parsley and hot pepper sauce.
Stuff shells.
Place in greased baking dish. Top with shredded cheese and tomato salsa.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: a man's cake(krydderkake)
directions: Cook together orange peel, 2 teaspoons sugar and the water. Cool.
Add melted butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs, sour cream and soda.
Sift together and add flour, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and nutmeg.
Bake in a bread pan in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until done.
This cake will keep fresh for a long time.

title: plum cake
directions: Stir with spoon.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: apple chicken salad(single serving)
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill until serving time.
Place on lettuce and serve.

title: walnut and apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat eggs and sugar for 5 minutes, or until sugar has dissolved and mixture is thick.
Keep beating and add oil, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Slowly add flour until batter is smooth and thick.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Pour batter in a greased
9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hot tomato-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Chop tomatoes and mix with chicken soup.
Lightly crush tortilla chips.
Layer all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole, beginning and ending with chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve as soon as possible.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice (drain if any water is left). Add eggs (beaten), vanilla, sugar, milk, raisins, butter and salt to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood deluxe
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper, garlic and chopped celery in margarine until wilted and onions are clear.
Add crab meat and shrimp; saute this until shrimp are pink.
Then add mushroom soup, red and black pepper, parsley, rice and salt.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: fiesta casserole(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook ground beef and onion until beef is browned.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and chili, stirring to break up tomato pieces.
Place tortilla chips in bottom; line sides of dish with large chips.
Spoon beef mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add red food coloring.
Chill and serve.

title: coal miner's pie
directions: In an iron skillet, brown beef and onions.
Drain well.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Mix the cornmeal and remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix the butter and Parmesan cheese; toss with spaghetti and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle 8 ounces Mozzarella cheese on top of spaghetti.
Put 1 layer of pepperoni on top of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce over pepperoni.
Put the remaining 8 ounces of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until warm and cheese is melted.

title: peanut cake
directions: Make 3 layers from cake mix.

title: white chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot except cheese.
Cook on low all day.
Just before serving, add cheese.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar and flour.
Blend until smooth.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, vanilla and milk. Add melted margarine and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 450° until lightly brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread in small cubes.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage; drain and crumble over bread. Sprinkle cheese on sausage.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: caring casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except marshmallows in large bowl. Mix well.
Place 1/2 of mixture in greased casserole.
Place 1 cup marshmallows evenly over all.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place remaining marshmallows on top. Bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Roll into a ball.
Roll cheese ball in chopped nuts.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mold a small amount of sweet potatoes around each marshmallow, completely surrounding it, before rolling it in crushed cornflakes (or, if preferred, a cornflake/crushed walnut mixture) and placing it in a 9 X 13-inch baking pan.
In a saucepan, melt butter, brown sugar and milk until smooth.
Drizzle the entire mixture over the sweet potato balls and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375 degrees, until brown and bubbly.

title: patricia's angel cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet covered with foil or sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove cookies from sheet while still warm. This recipe will make 36 cookies.
One cookie equals 89 calories.

title: beef-barbecue ribs or brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat in deep roasting pan.
Pour drinking coffee over meat.
Place meat, uncovered, in oven for 1 hour.
Then, pour barbecue sauce over top of meat.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Add caraway seed and onion soup mix.
Turn oven down to 300° for 3 hours or more.
Cover meat with aluminum foil or lid.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder, and cocoa (sift 3 times).
Add to mixture beginning with flour, liquid, flour.
Add vanilla with milk.
Blend until creamy.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake one hour and 30 minutes at 300°.
Let cool and remove cake from pan.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash potatoes.
Beat eggs; add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour mixture into mashed potatoes and blend well.
Stir in coconut, pecans and nutmeg.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and cover top with bacon.
Bake in slow oven two hours.

title: crock-pot bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours or on top of stove on low for 1 hour.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Form meat in small balls.
Brown lightly in small amount of shortening.
Drain.
Heat jelly and chili sauce until jelly melts and is heated through.
Pour into chafing dish; add meatballs. Serve warm.

title: chocolate, peanut butter, caramel cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Melt caramels, add some milk to this.
Spread peanut butter on a cracker; drop some caramel (from a spoon) on the peanut butter (not too much); place another cracker on top and press lightly.
Dip each cracker in melted chocolate (tongs work best); place on wax paper to harden.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not flour pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, cover with cream cheese frosting.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Saute onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add half and half and cook, stirring until sauce thickens.
Stir in cheese.
Add parsley and seasonings.
Combine sauce with potatoes. Turn into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grilled fish
directions: Combine olive oil, onion, cheese, basil, mustard, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper in blender.
Process 30 seconds.
Add vinegar and lemon juice; process additional 30 seconds.
Place fish in a grilling basket; grill over hot coals 10 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily, basting frequently with prepared sauce.
Remove fish to warm serving platter; garnish with lemon slices and serve with remaining sauce.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in flour, a little at a time.
Alternate eggs and flour.
Add flavoring.
Let eggs stand at room temperature for 1 hour before using.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Put batter in greased pan and bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Put peanut butter between the crackers.
Melt the almond bark about 2 minutes in the microwave.
Then spread the almond bark on the crackers, then let it dry.

title: hot and sweet beef and rice bundles(korean)
directions: Heat sesame oil in skillet and brown meat.
Drain.
Add chopped green onions, sherry or wine, chili paste, garlic, ginger, soy sauce and sugar.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle sesame seed over meat and serve with lettuce and rice.
Guests make their
own bundles filling a lettuce leaf with rice and meat mixture.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Step 1:
Combine flour and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Press flour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: one bowl white layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease three 8-inch or two 9-inch round pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line bottom of pans with waxed paper cut to fit.
Grease the paper and flour pans.
Thoroughly combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk and shortening and beat 2 minutes.
Add egg whites, vanilla and choice of extract.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into pans.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until inserted tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing.
Frost as desired.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together graham crackers and butter, then line pan with 2/3 of the crumbs.
Then mix together Cool Whip, vanilla, powdered sugar and miniature marshmallows.
On the crumb mixture, put a layer of the creamy mixture then add the can of pie filling, add the rest of the creamy mixture, then top with crumbs and chill.

title: meat loaf(using uncooked oats)
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: orange and cherry salad(serves 2)
directions: Remove white membrane from pulp of 2 oranges; cut each section in half, crosswise.
Add cherries, celery and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add salad dressing.
Serve very cold on lettuce leaves.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Brown
beef
with oil in skillet.
Add all ingredients, except carrots
and
potatoes and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Place carrots
and
potatoes in baking dish.
Top with meat mixture. Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon slowly.
Pour off most of grease and saute onions, then add flour, sugar, salt and mustard.
Stir over low heat. Stir vinegar and cold water into mixture over medium heat until thickened.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: In small saucepan, place peanut butter chips, milk and whipping cream. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Serve warm. Cover.
Refrigerate leftover sauce.

title: chocolate freeze pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into chocolate graham cracker crust.
Freeze.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Remove chicken from bone and place in frying pan with onion, stewed tomatoes, pepper, chili powder and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling.
Scoop mixture into corn tortillas; roll and place in shallow pan.
Pour remaining liquid from frying pan over tortillas.
Dollop sour cream over that and top with grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: chopstick beef
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients with beef.
Top with extra chow mein noodles.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: ginger dill dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, garlic and dill; mix together. Whisk good.
Add onion and ginger and blend until smooth.
Serve with your favorite chips or crackers.
Yields 1 cup.

title: black-eyed pea chowder
directions: Fry the sausage in a Dutch oven and drain; add remaining ingredients through the black pepper and then add half of the bell pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour, then add remaining bell pepper and potato.
Cook 30 minutes longer.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, put under broiler until bubbly and brown.
Serve with Tuscany Toast or any hard crackers.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Remove grease. Add other ingredients except sour cream. Simmer for 5 minutes. Add sour cream. Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: easy pattie dish
directions: Put patties in foil.
Top with potatoes, onions and carrots on top.
Wrap in foil and place in oven for 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and onto plates.
Serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: diabetic oat pancakes
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk, oil and lemon juice.
Pour into well and stir just until moistened.
Pour batter by 1/4 capfuls onto a lightly greased, hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles form on top.
Cook until second side is brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into casserole dish.
Top with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: confetti snack dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least an hour to blend flavors.
Serve as a dip with assorted crackers or other snacks. Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric beater and form into a ball. Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Roll in 1 cup chopped walnuts and serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and syrup.
Mix well.
Add oleo slowly and blend well.
Add pecans.
This makes 2 regular sized pies.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300°.

title: sugarless blueberry muffins
directions: Preparation tip:
Let all ingredients come to room temperature before starting.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in applesauce, milk, egg and oil.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan after cooling slightly.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Layer noodles, meat, cheese and sauce.
Repeat with cheese layer on top.
Sprinkle oregano over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Cut all fruit into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients except condensed milk and marshmallows.
Melt marshmallows and milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pack mixture into buttered loaf pan.
Cool, then turn out and cut.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown sausage and onion, then drain.
Mix together in a large pot both boxes of rice and seasoning packets, drained sausage and drained mushrooms.
Add 4 cups of water.
Bring to a boil on high temperature, then cover and reduce to simmer for 45 minutes.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Slowly melt the white chocolate in top of double boiler over simmering water. Combine cereals, pretzels, peanuts and M&M's in a large bowl. Slowly pour chocolate over mixture and stir to evenly coat. Spread the mixture on wax paper and cool. Break into small pieces. Store in airtight container and refrigerate to keep fresh.

title: corn chowder
directions: Chop and fry bacon until you have about a cup. Dip out bacon pieces and put aside. Saute onions until clear, add diced potatoes. Cover with water and cook until just tender. Add onion, corn, milk and butter. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: whipped jello
directions: Boil rice in 2 qts of water.
Drain and Cool.

title: taco pie
directions: Add all ingredients together and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Press rolls into a 9 x 13-inch pie plate.
Brown the turkey, onion and green pepper; drain if necessary.
Add taco seasoning (as much as you prefer).
Pour over rolls.
Pour and spread tomato puree over mixture; top with cheese.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Allow pie to cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions, pimentos and bell peppers; let stand for 1 hour.
Put remaining ingredients in spice bag and add the squash mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix flour, butter and milk together; set aside.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place vegetables, covering bottom of pan.
Spread chicken over vegetables.
Mix cream of chicken soup and broth together.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Pour flour mixture on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix all together and cook in crock-pot 4 to 6 hours.
Before serving, add crumbled bacon and stir in.

title: savory meat ball casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Shape by tablespoons into meat balls.
Brown, cover and cook 10 minutes. Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, 1 cup Pet milk and water.
Heat until steaming.
Pour over meat balls.
Top with Chili Cheese Biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: child's play popsicles
directions: Dissolve jello, kool aid and sugar in hot water. Add the cold water and freeze in ice cube trays. After adding ingredients to the ice cube tray, place a piece of plastic wrap over top of the tray and place toothpicks into kool aid for sticks.

title: wish-bone pork chops
directions: Marinate
chops
several hours.
Broil on grill outside or in oven, approximately 10 minutes on each side.

title: sister lisset's tea loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and add butter and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and beat in 2 cups sifted flour.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add bananas, oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple.
Stir to blend.
DO NOT BEAT.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.
Invert.
Does not need icing.

title: quick and easy fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake.

title: chalupa casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil; add chili powder and onions.
Simmer until onion is tender.
Add milk, tomato sauce and salt; simmer until hot.
Cut tortillas into 1/2 inch strips.
Arrange alternating layers of tortillas, meat mixture and cheese in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed and mix.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 250° until knife will come out clean when inserted into pie, about 40 minutes.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Skim loose skins.
Cook beans in same water.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Break bread in pieces and place in a buttered baking pan (9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch).
Arrange chicken, cut in pieces, on top of the bread.
Add water chestnuts.
Dot with mayonnaise and top with cheese.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Cream together until soft the cream cheese and sugar.
Roll into small balls.
Roll each ball in granulated sugar.
Flatten with forks or press in mold.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix together and layer with vanilla wafers.

title: oven barbecued venison
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper and brown in bacon fat with garlic.
Drain off fat.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours or until tender. Remove meat from pan and add rest of ingredients to juices. Remove to oven 1 hour or until thickened.
Slice meat, then add back to sauce and bake 30 minutes more.
Serve with rolls.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken over rice.
Spread soup on top of chicken.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over this, then add water and bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cover pan with foil.
Take foil off last 10 minutes.
After about 45 minutes, raise chicken up a little and stir rice so soup and moisture go to bottom and the rice isn't so dry.

title: peach delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients;
mix well and spread in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix sugar, flour and Jell-O well, then add water. Cook over medium heat until thick and clear; cool completely.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, 2/3 cup sugar and almond flavoring until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each at low speed.
Pour into an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Stir together sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of baked pie.
Cool.
Top with chocolate curls, almonds or fruit.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend all ingredients, adding pecan halves last.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center and edge comes out clean.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix white sugar, flour and cocoa.
Gradually add milk.
Add well beaten eggs, brown sugar, vanilla and butter.
Nuts may be added, if desired.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in preheated 325° oven until firm and shell is done.
Makes two 8-inch pies or 1 very large pie.

title: bourbon baked beans
directions: Mix beans, mustard, chili sauce, bourbon and strong coffee all together and let stand overnight.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: 7-up fruit mold
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle Knox gelatine over cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Stir in remaining fluids and sweetener. Chill mixture until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in fruit and pour into mold or 2-quart serving bowl.
Chill until firm.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: potato custard pie
directions: Boil potato.
Mash.
Add butter, sugar and salt; stir to creamy consistency.
Cool.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Mix well together.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: apple-nut salad
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together with a wire whisk, then add apples to mixture.
Add rest of the ingredients, as much or as little as you like.
Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into casserole.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until it looks set and is light brown on top.

title: quick chili
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add beef and cook over moderate heat, crumbling with a fork, until it loses its red color.
Stir in chili seasoning mix, then remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve in wide-rim soup plates with crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place 1 pie crust in pie dish or pan and brown lightly in oven.
Take chicken off the bone and add Veg-All (drained).
Add chicken soup, diluted with 1/4 can of chicken broth.
Stir and warm in microwave.
Pour into pie crust.
Place crust on top. Bake unti pie crust is done following cooking time on pie crust box.

title: christmas balls
directions: Mix all above ingredients.
Roll into small balls, then in powdered sugar.
Chill overnight.

title: vegetable delight
directions: Thinly slice all vegetables.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add potatoes and saute for 5 minutes.
Add onion, squash, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: fisherman salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Heat; let cool and pour over salad.
Let stand overnight.
Drain, if desired.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook and peel potatoes.
Boil water and sugar.
Add margarine, salt and vanilla. Place potatoes in a baking dish. Pour liquid over potatoes and bake about 1 hour.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; add onion and cook over low heat until onion is tender but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to steaming point and pour over leaf lettuce or spinach.
Serves 4.

title: ginger bread(in memory of mandy martin clemons)
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour together.
Mix together well. Then add sifted flour a little at a time.
Mix until dough forms a biscuit dough.
Roll out small cakes with hands.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: chicken rose
directions: Coat chicken with garlic salt, paprika and flour.
Brown in 1/2 cup oil.
Pour off excess, then add herbs and wine.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken. Stir sour cream into drippings and pour sauce over chicken.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dough on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread on cooled baked dough.

Cover with assorted vegetable toppings: 1 cup broccoli flowerets, 1 medium chopped onion (optional), 1/2 to 3/4 grated carrot, 1/2 cup chopped celery, 1/2 cup cauliflower tops, green peppers and black olives.

title: ragout of beef
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt, pepper and flour.
Brown well in the fat in a heavy pan.
While meat is browning, add the chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle with paprika; add hot water to cover.
Cover pan and cook slowly for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
If gravy is not thick enough, blend 1/2 tablespoon flour with a little cold water and stir into the stew.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
If additional seasoning is desired, add catsup, chili sauce or grated horseradish.

title: zucchini cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Add melted margarine and bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: easy hot mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of oven-safe dish.
Spread chili on top.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or microwave on High until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips for dipping.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Set off heat and add vanilla and oats (plus nuts if desired).
Mix well and place by teaspoons on wax paper.
Allow to cool, then place in airtight container.

title: microwave chili con cornbread
directions: Spread chili in an 8-inch square baking dish or other shallow 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and place dish on inverted saucer.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until hot, stirring after half the time.
Combine prepared cornbread batter and cheese.
Pour evenly over hot chili.
Tent corners of dish with foil.
Place dish on inverted saucer.
Microwave at Medium-high 5 to 7 minutes or until cornbread topping is even.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order with an electric mixer.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and cook at 350° until done.

title: butter cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix until stiff.
Drop from teaspoon and flatten onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken dish
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Stir twice during the hour.

title: seafood creole
directions: Cook vegetables in oil until tender.
Add tomato paste, water and seasonings. Simmer 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Add seafood and heat through.
Serve on hot rice.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix by hand first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix together.
Place in greased 1 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar thoroughly. Add 1 whole egg at a time alternately with the flour. Beat 1 minute after adding each egg. Add vanilla and continue beating about 2 minutes.
Pour into ungreased stem pan and bake for about 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
I like to add 1 teaspoon almond flavoring.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops. Remove from pan. In same pan, pour soup. Add 1/2 cup water. Layer chops, potatoes and onion in baking dish. Pour soup over this. Cover and bake 3/4 hour at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: rice-pecan stuffing
directions: Cook rice according to box directions, substituting bouillon for water (include seasoning packets).
Melt margarine in skillet. Add onion, celery and parsley.
Saute onion, celery and parsley over low heat until tender, stirring frequently.
Combine with cooked rice, pecans, giblets and seasonings.
Toss together lightly.
Bake in large dish at 350° until hot.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to a softball stage.
Take off stove. Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Stir until mixed well. Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9 dish or pan.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Make a paste of the cocoa and red food coloring. Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix salt and vanilla with buttermilk. Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour. Blend soda with vinegar. Fold into mixture. Do not beat.
Pour batter into 2 prepared 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost as desired.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Add the okra last.
Drop by tablespoon into hot peanut oil until golden.

title: surprise!  salad or dessert
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour into serving dish.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.
Can be used as a salad or dessert.
My favorite is blueberry pie filling and use almonds instead of pecans.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients except flour with the warm cottage cheese.
Add
flour
gradually
to mix.
Stir well.
Cover and let rise in
warm place 1 hour.
Stir down.
Turn into greased bowl or casserole.	Rise
minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. You can brush butter on top while still warm.

title: coney island casserole
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise and mustard together.
Pour over rice mixture and toss lightly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sugar-flour paste
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Slowly stir in 1 cup of cold water. Bring remaining 3 cups to a boil and add dry mixture to it, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook in double boiler for about 30 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add oil of cloves.
Makes 1 quart of paste.
Keep moist by adding a small piece of wet sponge to the top of each jar.

title: rice and chicken jambalaya(meal in a dish)
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter in a 2-quart saucepan until golden brown.
Add broth, rice and seasonings.
Cover.
Cook over low heat about 20 minutes.
Add chicken and carrots and cook 15 more minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: wham and rice croquettes
directions: Cook rice.
Mix together celery soup, ground wham, rice, onion, green pepper and mustard.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into croquettes using about 1/4 cup per croquette.
Dip in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.
Let stand a few minutes.
Fry 2 or 3 at a time in deep fat at 365° for 3 to 5 minutes or until brown. Drain on paper towels.
Prepare frozen peas according to package directions.
Pour over croquettes and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: three week slaw
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; let stand while preparing remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
White hot, pour over cabbage mixture and stir.
This slaw will keep for 3 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: sausage chicken casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Drain off fat.
Add veggies and saute until crisp-tender.
Combine soup mix, rice and water in a saucepan.
Cook 20 minutes.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Add sausage and soup mixture, stirring to mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Sprinkle with almonds; cover.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: rolls
directions: Scald milk and oleo in a large pot (Dutch oven).
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, yeast and 4 cups of flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining 4 cups flour.
Mix. Place cover on the pot.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down.
Place on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased (Crisco) cookie sheets.
Cover with dish towels free from draft.
Let rise about 45 minutes. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Brush tops with melted butter.
Yield: 72 rolls.

title: karen's coleslaw dressing
directions: Beat all of the above until thick.

title: zucchini and mushroom soup
directions: In a large heavy kettle, saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add zucchini and salt.
Saute 10 to 15 minutes or until zucchini is almost soft.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 2 minutes or until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Heat through.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Prepare frozen artichokes as package directs.
Do not overcook.
Drain the artichokes and place on bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
Squeeze as much water as possible from the thawed spinach and layer it on top of the artichokes.

title: spicy honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise with orange juice and mustard.
Slowly whisk in honey, adding horseradish last.
Serve with thin slices of beef or ham.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook spaghetti; brown onions and peppers in fat.
Add meat; stir until gray.
Stir in other ingredients with spaghetti; pour into greased casserole.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions. Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes. While baking, melt caramels with milk and butter over low heat; stir constantly.
Pour over cake (baked half).
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips over caramel.
Pour remaining cake batter over filling; sprinkle 1 cup nuts on top.
Bake another 25 minutes.
Check with toothpick.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone. Cut meat into small pieces. Mix chicken with all other ingredients except Doritos which are used to line the baking dish and crumble some to top casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poor man or eggless cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in ingredients.
Put salad oil in one hole, vinegar in second hole and vanilla in third hole.
Pour water over all.
Mix with fork until it is like cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix and pour this over mixture already in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sticky buns
directions: Melt butter.
Place frozen rolls in bottom of tube or Bundt pan after greasing bottom and sides of pan.
Pour butter over rolls. Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nuts and top with butterscotch pudding. Let rise overnight on counter and bake in the morning. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: janet bowman's breakfast pizza
directions: Spread roll dough onto bottom of baking pan with tall sides. Brown sausage and drain.
Spread over dough.
Cover sausage with hash browns, probably will not take whole bag.
Add beaten, seasoned eggs, you may not need 7.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 425°.
If using a "brownie pan" it may take 40 minutes.
Cut and serve warm.

title: cheese and crab stuffed mushrooms(servings:  6)
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and set caps aside; chop stems. In small skillet, saute onion and chopped stems in butter until tender.
Add bread cubes and crab; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Add salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Fill mushroom caps with bread stuffing. Place in 9-inch square or shallow baking dish.
Pour wine around caps.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Continue baking 8 to 10 minutes until cheese melts.
(To make ahead, prepare, cover and refrigerate.
Bake as directed.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma's peanut butter "quickies"
directions: That's "it."
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely when baking.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots lengthwise; cook until tender.
Drain well.
Melt margarine in skillet; add lemon juice and brown sugar.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Add carrots and stir until well glazed and heated through.

title: cauliflower puffs
directions: Separate cauliflower florets;
wash and boil just until tender (don't
overcook).
In
a deep bowl, beat eggs and add remaining ingredients
to
form a smooth batter.
Put florets into
batter and,
with
large
spoon,
scoop
up one by one, florets
and batter, and drop into hot oil in frying pan. Turn while
cooking to brown evenly.
When golden brown, remove and drain on paper towel.
Serve when still warm.

title: festive tostada bake
directions: Brown beef with green pepper and onion.
Drain well.
Add green olives and seasonings.
Place in shallow ovenproof casserole.
Spoon sour cream over meat, then pour beans evenly over sour cream.
Sprinkle corn chips then cheese over beans. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 15 to 20 minutes until heated through and cheese is melted.
Serve plain or over shredded lettuce or hot rice.

title: pizza toast
directions: Spread bread slices with pizza sauce.
(A good spaghetti sauce may be used.)
Add pepperoni, cheese and any other desired toppings.
Place in preheated oven, 450°, just until cheese is melted.

title: german nut cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add eggs.
Add rest of ingredients. Fold in nuts and cherries.
Bake in well-greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Very good.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter (softened) and 2 eggs together with mixer.
Batter should be stiff.
Spoon into 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Spread evenly.
Mix cream cheese until smooth; add eggs and powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Should be lightly browned.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add soda to flour.
Alternate flour and sour cream to creamed mixture. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: 24-hour bean salad
directions: Mix together green beans, kidney beans, celery, green pepper and pimiento.
Mix well sugar, vinegar, oil, water, salt and paprika and pour over salad.
Chill and drain before serving.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Cook chopped broccoli; drain.
Mix milk, soup and broccoli; heat, adding cheese to taste.

title: lasagna(student favorite)
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat and rinse meat.
Add next five ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount boiling water until tender (approximately 10 minutes); drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Place one-half of the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half the cottage cheese filling, half of the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
(If refrigerated, allow an extra 15 minutes or so in the oven.)

title: watermelon preserves
directions: Pare and cut watermelon rind into pieces 2-inches long and 3/4-inch wide.
Cover with brine made from salt dissolved in 1 quart water; let stand overnight.
Drain; cover with water and boil 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cover with heavy syrup of equal parts water and sugar and thinly sliced lemon to each 3 quarts rind. Cook slowly until rind is tender and clear.
Put in jars and seal.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put butter, sugar, cocoa and milk in microwave.
Cook for 2 minutes on High.
Remove.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir and pour in buttered pan.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Drain well and mash fine.
Grate onion and saute in butter until done.
Mix all ingredients; chill.
Make into croquettes and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: raisin squares
directions: You will need one 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch size pan.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: In a pie or quiche pan, spread refried beans on the bottom, then guacamole, yogurt and salsa.
Top with chopped onion, shredded Cheddar and tomato.
Spread sliced black olives for decoration.
Serve chilled.
Eat with chips.

title: quick chicken and vegetable stew
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, cut each chicken leg at joint.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken a few at a time until well browned on all sides. Remove chicken to plate as they brown.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Cook carrots until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Return chicken; add tomato sauce, water, sugar, salt, oregano and pepper.
Over high heat bring to boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add broccoli; over high heat, heat to boiling, separating broccoli with a fork. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Skim fat and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas with red sauce
directions: In a boiler, liquefy the tomatoes, onion, garlic and chilies. In 1/4 cup of oil, fry mixture.
In the other 1/4 cup oil, fry the tortillas until soft.
Coat the tortillas with the sauce. Fill with chicken and roll up.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and heat in oven.
Serve with sour cream, cheese and onions for garnish on top.
Serves 8.

title: danish apple pie(for microwave)
directions: Place apple slices in a large mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon; add to apples and stir to coat.
Pour apples into baked pastry shell; spread evenly.
Mix together remaining ingredients for topping and sprinkle over apples.
Cook on High until apples are fork tender.
Cool before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, salt, dry pudding, oleo, egg and milk.
Mix like cake batter.
Pour onto greased, unfloured 9-inch pie pan.
Drain peaches and arrange evenly over batter in pan.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and juice.
Beat until thick.
Pour into center of peaches to within 1-inch of sides. Sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Keep in tightly closed container.
Use three heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix squash,
crumbs,
onions,
egg, sage, salt and pepper and turn into
casserole
dish.
Pour
remaining melted butter over the top and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients with wet.

title: italian beef stir-fry
directions: Cook garlic in oil in large non-stick skillet for 1 minute. Add beef strips, stir-fry 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove beef; add zucchini to same skillet.
Stir-fry until tender.
Return beef to skillet with tomato halves and dressing.
Heat through.
Serve mixture over hot pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
4 servings.

title: pasta seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients. Sprinkle on cooked pasta.
Can be stored in the refrigerator. It's also good sprinkled on salads.
Yields 4 servings (1 tablespoon each), 20 calories, fat free.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet. Crumble. Add vinegar, brown sugar, salt and onion. Heat thoroughly. Add 1/2 cup water and cabbage.
Cover and steam until tender.

title: after school snack
directions: Spread one tablespoon of peanut butter on each slice of bread to cover completely.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of granola and 1 tablespoon of chocolate chips evenly over peanut butter.
Serves two.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Combine in the	order
given, stirring after each addition. Boil until thick.
Cool before adding to the salad.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and chill before serving.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cake or	package of dry yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm
water.
Add
teaspoon sugar.
Into a large mixing bowl put
cup sugar, salt, fat, egg and 1 cup warm water. Beat
thoroughly.
Add
gradually, about 4 cups flour.
Knead. Put into
a
warm
place
to rise until double in bulk.
Press down and place in icebox until needed.

title: homemade eagle brand milk(1930)
directions: Put in blender and blend until smooth.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.
Great recipe for lemon icebox pies and homemade ice cream.

title: peanut bread
directions: Sift flour 3 times with soda and salt.
Blend sugar and peanut butter.
Stir in egg and beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately, beating after each addition.
Bake in greased pan at 350° until well browned (about 1 hour).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake in bowl and beat for 3 minutes. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (grease and flour not necessary).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Arrange crescent rolls in a 10-inch pie pan with points to the center.
Brown sausage; drain well.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add sausage, then pour in pie pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: old-fashioned apple cake
directions: In one bowl, sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. In a large bowl, mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Add the sifted ingredients. Fold in apple, nuts and chocolate chips. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fruktsoppa (dessert soup)
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; let stand for 10 minutes.
Add cinnamon, orange, lemon, sugar and tapioca; bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook until the apples are tender (about 5 minutes).
Take out the cinnamon stick.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Also good with fresh blueberries or blackberries.

title: cheese balls
directions: Use directions on back of Ranch dressing package, only use 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 of the mayonnaise it calls for.
Let Cheddar cheese sit for one hour at room temperature.
Mix 1/2 cup of dressing with cream cheese, then stir in shredded cheese.
Cover bowl and freeze for 30 minutes.
Then roll into a ball.
Then roll in the almonds.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate-covered cherry cookies
directions: In
a
large
mixing
bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder,
soda
and	salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine with an electric mixer on medium speed 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat on low until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla;
beat well.
Gradually
add
flour mixture to beaten mixture, beating on low until well blended.

title: ghostly glow punch
directions: Mix juices and chill.
Garnish with orange slices and cherries.
Serves 12.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Melt brown sugar and butter; stir.
Boil 1 minute.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into loaf and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate carrots and onion.
(Amount varies to how much salad you want.)
Mix together.
Crumble a few crackers into carrots and onion mixture. Add sugar, salt and pepper to taste and mayonnaise. You can add raisins or apples, if desired.

title: cherry-topped cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 way up the sides of a greased 9-inch round spring-form pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spinach lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna; rinse and drain.
Arrange noodles flat on an oiled surface.
Combine salad dressing with cream cheese.
Mix half of this mixture with spinach; spread 2 tbsp. of the spinach mixture over each noodle.
From narrow end, roll up each noodle and place seam side down in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Whisk tomato sauce and milk into remaining cream cheese mixture.
When smooth, pour sauce over roll-ups.
Cover with foil and bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover loosely and bake for 10 minutes longer or until hot and bubbly.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream together butter and confectioners sugar, then add 2 teaspoons water, brandy flavor, walnuts and flour.
Mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
While still hot, roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: nora's chicken supreme
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add sugar to melted shortening and 1 tablespoon of hot water.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and flour; mix gradually.
Mix well. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips over top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until golden brown).
Cool and cut.

title: fruit salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pudding, jello, tapioca and liquids, stirring constantly, for about 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Pour over fruit.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
In a separate bowl add the boiling water to molasses, soda and cinnamon.
Beat mixture until foamy.
Stir 1/2 of crumb mixture into molasses mixture and pour into pie shell.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until pie is firm and lightly brown.

title: chicken fantasia
directions: Wash chicken, cut in half and put in casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and heat until hot and onion begins to soften slightly. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Add egg and cocktail. Mix all ingredients together. Do not use electric mixer. Bake in 2 layers or in 1 (9 1/2 x 5-inch) pan at 375°.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: First Step:
Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, but add vegetables with seasoning packet.
Combine soup, milk and parsley; set aside.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°, then cover with foil.
Bake 25 minutes longer.

title: chicken in lemon and capers
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Dredge in flour.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown chicken in oil, both sides.
Remove to warm oven.
Add bouillon and wine to skillet.
Reduce some and add juice of 1/2 lemon.
Add back chicken.
Top with thinly sliced lemon and rosemary.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with capers and warm 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips in a small baking dish. Sprinkle chips on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: you name it cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, lemon-lime soda and oil; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When almost done, make icing.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco, then sugar, then eggs, one at a time. Add flour and baking powder.
Add milk and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: czech potato dumplings
directions: Mix eggs, flour and salt with mashed potatoes.
If potatoes are very moist, use more flour as needed.
Place dough on a floured board, roll out to a thickness for cutting 15 dumplings. Bring large kettle of water to boil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt. Drop dumplings into water and boil for 8 minutes.

title: g.g.'s ginger crisp
directions: Heat molasses to the boiling point.
Remove from flame.
Add shortening and stir until shortening is melted.
When cold, add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll very thin.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a moderately hot oven at 375° for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef (drain fat).
Add all ingredients; put in crock-pot.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Heat shortening in large skillet until melted.
Cook and stir beef and onion in shortening until beef is brown and onion is tender.
Add water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 50 minutes. Heat oven to 350°.
Pour beef mixture into ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Arrange potato slices on beef. Mix soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper; pour on potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cereal.
Bake uncovered until potatoes and beef are tender, 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: irene's dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a square or oblong glass dish.
Freeze.
Let thaw a little before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan 10 x 4-inches. Beat sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla in a large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly every 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 2 minutes.
Beat in flour, salt and baking soda alternately with sour cream on low speed.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean; 80 to 90 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt in double boiler 32 caramels, cream and butter.
Mix together butter and sugar.
Add flour, soda, salt and oatmeal. Press 3/4 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Pour caramel sauce over crust.
Add chocolate chips and chopped walnuts.
Pour remaining crumbs over top.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Serve cold in tall glass sprinkled lightly with nutmeg.
Makes 1 serving.

title: banana split pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except crusts and beat at least 10 minutes with mixer.
Place in 2 graham cracker crusts. Slice 2 bananas on each pie.
Layer crushed pineapple (drained) on top of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cook onion until wilted in butter.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, oleo and eggs together.
Blend well. Add salt, baking powder, nutmeg, lemon flavoring and vanilla. Dissolve baking soda into buttermilk.
Add buttermilk and flour. Blend well.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Add crumbs and chicken; beat until smooth.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
May be turned out onto platter or sliced in pan.
Dilute cream of mushroom soup with milk; heat and spoon over each slice.

title: chocolate sour cream brunch cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, sour cream, eggs, oil, vanilla and pudding mix in large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until tests done.
Cool 25 minutes before removing from pan.
(May bake in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan for 25 minutes or until tests done.) May sprinkle powdered sugar on cake or ice or glaze with your favorite icing.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare the gelatin according to directions on package.
When cool, add the pineapple.
Do not add juice from can.
Add the carrot.
Place in refrigerator in small containers or in mold to gel.
When ready to serve, place on lettuce leaf topped with mayonnaise.

title: frosty fruit cup
directions: Mix ingredients together and freeze.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender or food processor until fine. Mix pudding according to directions on package. Cream sugar and cream cheese together. Blend in pudding and Cool Whip. Layer cookies and pudding mixture in a clean clay or plastic flowerpot, starting with cookies and ending with cookies. (You may want to add "gummy worms" throughout layers for "effects.") Decorate top layer with "gummy worms" and add decorative wooden or plastic flowers.

title: oniony potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and simmer covered for 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain, reserving liquid. Add 3/4 cup of liquid to potatoes and mash.
Add more cooking liquid to thin if necessary.

title: rhubarb rosettes
directions: Simmer sugar and water together 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered baking dish, 9 x 12-inch.
Mix sliced and chopped rhubarb with strawberry gelatin and set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut butter until crumbly.
Beat egg with milk and stir into flour mixture to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface and roll out to 13 x 9-inch.
Brush with melted butter.
Add any juice from rhubarb mixture to syrup in baking dish.
Spread rhubarb over dough and roll up like a jelly roll. Cut into about a dozen slices and place a top of syrup.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cold milk or ice cream.

title: coconut bar dessert
directions: Line long dish with coconut cookie bars.
Cream 1 stick oleo and 1 cup powdered sugar; spread over cookies.
Drain good and spread over that 1 cup crushed pineapple.
Lay another layer of cookies over pineapple.
Spread over that 2 packages cherry jello that has been partially set.
Chill until firm and spread with a layer of Cool Whip.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in baking dish.
Top with 1 tube Ritz crackers, crushed and mixed with 1 stick oleo.
Put on top of vegetable mix and bake for 25 minutes at 250° or until brown.
Serves 10.

title: ranch salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add Fritos at last minute and toss.

title: spinach romanoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package and drain.
Cook spinach and drain.
Combine the noodles, spinach, onions and margarine.
Then mix together sour cream and Romanoff packet mix.
Add to noodles and spinach mixture.
Place mixture into a greased glass baking dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: All ingredients must be at room temperature.

title: scramble
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes or so.
Makes 8 quarts.
Store in tightly covered can.
Will keep for a long time.

title: potato pancakes (latkes)
directions: Grate the potatoes and onion in a large mixing bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir the batter well.
Preheat a frying pan to 325° with a generous amount of low-fat cooking oil.
Using a serving spoon, carefully place the batter in the frying pan and cook until the pancakes are golden brown.
Serve with either cinnamon and sugar, applesauce or sour cream.

title: v-8 tomato juice
directions: Simmer to boil, then can.

title: healthy crab dip
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasonings.
Mix well.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover; chill for 2 hours.

title: bean and canadian bacon soup
directions: Heat oil; add carrot and onion and saute about 5 minutes.
Add bacon; saute 5 minutes longer.
Add beans, broth, oregano and bay leaves.
Bring to boil; reduce and simmer, covered, until beans are tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Preferable to refrigerate soup a day before serving.

title: russian meadavuka
directions: Add 1/2 liter of water to the honey, bring to a boil and skim. Pour into a flask or barrel, add the cranberry juice, cinnamon, cloves and yeast and set aside to ferment for two days.
Cover the flask or barrel and set aside in a cool place for about three weeks.
After this pour into bottles and seal.

title: sour cream vegetable dip(low fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Serve with raw vegetables such as celery, carrots, cauliflower, broccoli, mushrooms and green pepper.

title: sausage gravy and biscuits
directions: Brown and crumble sausage.
With slotted spoon, remove sausage and drain well.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons fat.
To the fat, add flour and mix until smooth.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Keep stirring until you have a smooth gravy.
Add the sausage and Au Jus mix, if desired.

title: fiesta chicken rolls
directions: Pound each raw chicken piece with a meat hammer to flatten. Mix 3 tablespoons butter and cheese spread until well blended. Mix in onion and salt.
Divide mixture equally onto the 6 flattened chicken pieces, placing a portion at one end of each piece.
Roll up, tucking in ends to completely enclose filling. Fasten rolls with wooden toothpicks or tie with string.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in 1 1/2-quart glass dish in microwave oven. Coat and roll with melted butter.
Mix crumbs and taco seasonings together.
Roll the butter covered chicken in crumb mix to cover. Arrange rolls in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge candy
directions: Put sugar, milk and butter in large pan and bring to a boil. Let boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from fire. Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar, nutmeats and vanilla. Beat until all is dissolved. Add marshmallow cream. Stir mixture until well blended. Pour in buttered pans. Cut when cold. Makes 5 pounds candy.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain off fat.
Boil vegetables until tender.
Mix ground beef, onions, soup, celery seed, tomatoes and flour.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In baking dish, mix vegetables with meat mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: other tortilla rolls
directions: Mix altogether and spread on flour tortilla.
Roll up and cut in 1-inch sections.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients together and slowly add to mixture; beat well.

title: cool whip pudding cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Combine butter, 1/2 cup nuts and flour (or graham crumbs); mix thoroughly.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and press mixture into pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the rotini according to package; rinse and drain.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain corn and peas.
Set aside.
Chop onions and jalapeno. Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Use electric mixer. In large bowl, cream Crisco, granulated sugar and brown sugar. Beat until fluffy. Then beat in eggs and vanilla. In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 minutes on center rack of oven.
