title: potato salad roll
directions: Pare, cook and mash potatoes (not creamy, but lumpy); do not add any liquid. Combine with 1/3 cup mayonnaise, the salt and paprika. Stir in celery, eggs and onions. Chill.

title: spicy peach pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix; add spices and in a saucepan, cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil. Cool 5 minutes; stir twice.
Chill 10 minutes.
Fold in peaches. Pour into pie shell.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate and combine all.
Roll in pecans.
Makes 2 balls.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well. Combine flour, soda and sugar.
Add to banana mixture, stirring until well blended.
Stir in pecans, coconut and raisins.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Cover with foil the last 15 minutes of baking to prevent overbrowning, if necessary.

title: quickie cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Melt 1/2 cup margarine or butter and add 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder; pour over hot biscuits and serve.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar and salt and cream.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Mix milk and flavorings.
Alternate flour and milk mixture into other ingredients.
Pour into a prepared Bundt pan and bake for one hour and twenty minutes at 325°.

title: french apple pie
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon with the apples.
Arrange in pie shell and dot with 1 1/2 teaspoons of butter.
Make a mixture of 1/2 cup of butter, brown sugar and flour.
Put on apples and bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Top with Butter Icing.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Peel and core tomatoes.
Cut tomatoes in half crosswise. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise, nutmeg and dill.
Pour this mixture over tomatoes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until tomatoes are tender.

title: strawberry pie(for 2)
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add Jell-O and cool.
Cook 2 pie crusts.
After Jell-O mixture is completely cool, fill each pie crust with fresh strawberries.
Pour mixture over berries.
Let stand in refrigerator 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt onto wax paper.
Melt butter in a medium-size saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat; beat in sugars, egg and vanilla with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture and apples (add 1/2 cup of chopped walnuts if desired) until thoroughly combined. Spread onto a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of Cinnamon Sugar.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes or until top springs when lightly pressed.
Cool on wire rack.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mom's clam dip
directions: Drain clams; save juice.
Mix all ingredients together, adding juice for desired consistency.
Chill before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake according to package.
Cool.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Beat ingredients all together in blender until thick.

title: ham and red eye gravy
directions: Cover ham with water and bring to a boil to remove excess salt. Drain off water and add fat (bacon drippings may be used). Fry gently until done; not hard. Remove ham to a platter.
Add a little water to pan, stirring any brown that stuck to the pan. Add coffee.
Pour over ham in platter and serve with rice, grits or biscuits.

title: mother's day brunch baked spanish eggs
directions: Saute the onions and pepper in the butter until lightly browned.
Place evenly on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Carefully break the eggs, keeping the yolks intact, placing them evenly in the pan over the onion/green pepper mixture.

title: low calorie dressing(for diabetics)
directions: Place lid on jar and shake until well blended.
Place and keep in refrigerator.

title: toffee coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except last 3) for 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of cake batter into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Top with a can of French fried onion rings.
Place in casserole dish and bake 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and boil all ingredients, then let simmer for awhile.

title: creamy ham bake
directions: Cook noodles separately.
In a large skillet, melt butter. Add celery, green pepper, onion and salt.
Cook until tender. Blend in soup and milk; stir in cheese, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Combine egg noodles, soup mixture and ham.
Mix well.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 20-30 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain in large kettle.
Add all ingredients. Bring to boil; lower heat and cook until onions are tender, stirring constantly.
Spaghetti may be added, if desired.
Serve hot.

title: pasta pesto
directions: Blend basil leaves, garlic, pine nuts, and olive oil in blender to make a paste.
Cook pasta to taste, al dente is recommended.
Toss drained pasta with paste while still hot.
Add Parmesan cheese and toss again.
Serves 4 as a main dish or 6 as a side dish.
Refrigerate leftovers immediately.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Melt butter and stir into peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Roll into small balls (melon baller works well); refrigerate for 2 hours or freeze for 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll out dough on lightly floured board to about 1/3-inch thick. Spread generously with Crisco, then sugar, then cinnamon and raisins and nuts.
Roll up dough. Cut 1-inch thick and lay, cut side down, on well-greased pan very loosely. Bake at 350° for about 18 minutes.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and serve cold.
Makes 1 generous cup.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Make the whipped topping according to package directions, using milk and vanilla.
Stir in the pineapple, pecans, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: hidden valley ranch stars
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Brush wonton wrappers with oil (both sides).
Bake in muffin pans for 5 minutes at 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Set aside until ready to serve.
Place baked wontons on cookie sheet and fill with filling.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and cream until light.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix applesauce with flour mixture alternately.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° until tester is clean. Will make four 6 x 3-inch cakes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening until smooth.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture gradually.
Add vanilla, bran flakes, oatmeal and coconut. Form mixture into small balls; place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Remove from oven; let set about 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix 1 cup salt and 2 quarts water.
Pour over vegetables and let stand 1 hour.
Boil 3 cups sugar and 2 cups white vinegar until syrup (about 3 minutes).
Put vegetables in and let come to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Put in jars and seal.

title: easy lemon cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian rice and cheesecake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together for 1 minute.
Mix mashed Ricotta cheese with milk, wine, rind and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture. Stir in cooked rice.
Turn into well-greased square baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: cheese soup(serves 6 to 12)
directions: Melt the margarine and saute the onions, celery and carrot until veggies are limp.
Add the chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add the potato soup, Cheddar cheese, parsley, Tabasco sauce and salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream.
Simmer 15 minutes. Do not boil.
Add sherry.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine the ingredients in a bowl and beat with a fork or mixer until as thick as heavy whipped cream.
Place in a small serving bowl and garnish with crisp relishes such as radishes, celery,
carrot strips, pickles and olives.

title: easy potato-sausage casserole
directions: Brown crumbled sausage in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Layer potatoes, sausage and cheese in baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and pepper.
Pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle more cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Soften butter and cheese to room temperature.
Mix butter and cheese with hands.
Add dry ingredients with hands.
Add nuts. Roll like pepperoni.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Slice with sharp knife.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Mix pudding according to box.
Take Cool Whip and cover inside of dish, spreading evenly (sides and bottom).
Add pudding to center.

title: stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Mix with remaining ingredients and shape into balls.
Place in pan.
Put small amount of water on bottom of pan to prevent sticking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add water to bottom during cooking time as needed.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add grated carrots, oil, pineapple, beaten eggs, nuts, coconut and rest.
Bake in pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: oyster crackers
directions: In
a
large bowl mix all ingredients (except crackers) together thoroughly.
Add crackers and stir until all crackers are coated.
Spread
on
cookie
sheet and bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: pizza crust
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water; stir until dissolved.
Add 2 tablespoons vegetable oil and 4 cups flour; stir with wooden spoon until all flour is moistened.
Knead on a lightly floured surface. Knead in remaining flour until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Place in medium bowl; brush lightly with vegetable oil.
Cover with towel; let rise in warm place (about 85°) until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
Punch down dough; divide in half.
Each half will make a 14-inch pizza crust.
Top as desired.
Let set 10 minutes as oven heats to 425°.
Bake for about 20 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.

title: horseradish cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to stand at room temperature to soften. Work cream cheese with hands until softened.
Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Must be chilled for 24 hours before serving.
If desired, just before serving, roll onto bacon or pecan bits.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix with hands until creamy; will take a while.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 4 days.

title: company mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.

title: beef-vegetable stew
directions: Season beef cubes with salt, then dredge meat with flour. Brown beef in the shortening.
Remove beef to large kettle.
Add the water and bouillon cubes.
Cover; bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.
Cut celery, potatoes, carrots and onion into 1-inch pieces; add to meat.
Add salt.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 40 to 45 minutes in a covered kettle.
Add tomatoes; simmer 20 minutes.
Serve hot with corn bread.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix in bowl the soup, mayonnaise, egg, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
After broccoli is done, place in bottom of baking dish.
Pour mixture over broccoli. Place Cheddar cheese over mixture.
Then place croutons on top. Cover and bake at 350° until croutons are brown.

title: tahitian coffee cake
directions: Combine pineapple, brown sugar, 1/4 cup butter or margarine, cinnamon and syrup.
Cook over medium heat until mixture starts to boil.
Spoon into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Slice banana.
Measure water into warm bowl.
Crumble or sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Cream remaining butter or margarine with white sugar and salt.
Add eggs, milk and yeast mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in flour.
Spoon carefully over pineapple mixture, let rise in warm place free from draft until double in size, about 1 hour.
Bake in oven at 375° for 40 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan for 15 minutes then remove.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix.

title: bean dip
directions: In a quiche-size casserole dish, layer the refried beans. Press them firmly into the bottom of the dish.
Top the beans with the salsa.
Sprinkle the shredded Cheddar cheese on next.
Bake 5 minutes in microwave on High.
Divide sour cream up into 4 to 5 spoonfuls and dollop on top of Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with black olives.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Beat eggs well in large mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients except zucchini and mix well.
Fold in zucchini and mix until well coated.
Put mixture in greased pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup vegetable shortening.
Add 1 pound sugar (use light brown with the banana cake) when well mixed.
Slowly add warm milk (1/2 regular and 1/2 canned Pet milk).
Add slowly to prevent curdling.
Combine 2 tablespoons whole wheat flour and 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar and add this to the frosting mixture and beat until creamy.

title: frozen banana split
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish. Freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: never-fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs with milk.
Mix liquid with dry ingredients.
Add cubed bread and mix again.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Make 2 balls and roll each in flour.
Place balls into boiling water and boil for 10 minutes.
Turn over and boil for 15 more minutes.
Cut one in half and check if done. When done, take out and slice.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Peel the onions; parboil in boiling, salted water with the butter.
Drain and cool.
Carefully scoop out the center part of each onion and chop very fine with half its quantity of chopped mushrooms.
Put in a saucepan with the cup of bread crumbs, salt, pepper and nutmeg, then add the white sauce.
Mix well and stuff the center of the onions with this mixture.
Place onions on buttered tin.
Sprinkle the tops with bread crumbs.
Put a small piece of butter on each one and bake in a moderate oven for 1/2 hour.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade and Cool Whip.
Mix Eagle Brand with lemonade concentrate.
Combine with Cool Whip; pour into graham cracker crusts and serve.

title: pea salad
directions: In long deep dish, layer lettuce, peas and onion. Sprinkle cheese over thin layer of mayonnaise. Spread over onion.
Cut up eggs over cheese. Top with bacon pieces that have been fried and drained. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: squash pie(makes 2)
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and when cool, mash. Mix eggs, sugar, flour and flavoring real good. Blend in margarine and squash. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: mary jo reeves' ham and swiss party sandwiches
directions: Blend margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce to make a spread.
Cut rolls in half.
Spread margarine mixture on each cut half.
Place small amount of ham and cheese on bottom of each roll.
Cover with top half of roll.
Wrap in foil and place on baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 60 appetizer sandwiches.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add chopped crab meat, celery and green onions.
Mix well and serve with crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
When ready to serve, break up sherbet and add.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: dessert supreme
directions: Mix and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook at 300° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: In a bowl, beat egg white until foamy. Add pecans and toss until well coated. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over pecans and toss to coat. Spread in a single layer on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until browned. Cool on waxed paper.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon; remove any skin and bones.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke.
Mix well.
I sometimes mush it with my hands, then form into a ball.
Chill several hours.

title: savory squash
directions: Cook squash and onion in a small amount of water; drain well. Combine with rice, cheese and seasonings.
Blend in eggs and mayonnaise; stir into vegetable mixture.
Turn into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy frosting
directions: Cook in double boiler until it starts to thicken.

title: mike's mush
directions: Pour milk into glass.
Crush graham crackers and add to milk. Mix until creamy.

title: continental chicken
directions: Grease crock-pot.
Arrange
dried
beef
on
bottom and sides of crock-pot.
Wrap
bacon	around	chicken;
place
on beef.
Mix soup according to directions and pour over chicken. Cook on low 7 to 9 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Add sour cream last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: chinese chewies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, then flour and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for about 40 minutes.
They will look like they fell.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine top five ingredients, then fold in sour cream.
Pour in shallow baking dish and top with grated cheese before baking.

title: running chocolate cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake per instructions on box, adding Crisco (optional).
Pour into 3 layer pans.
Bake per instructions. Prepare Chocolate Icing.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan well.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam spray.
Lay crescent rolls flat in pan.
Cook sausage, drain all grease.
Place over uncooked crescent rolls; top with hash browns, Cheddar cheese, onions and green and red peppers.
Combine eggs with milk.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until egg mixture is completely firm.
Let cool for 5 to 10 minutes and enjoy.

title: sausage soup
directions: Slice fried sausage and add other ingredients to pot.
You may use water, tomato juice or any other broth to cover.
Cook 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Use your imagination for different varieties like chicken or beef or pasta, etc.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, coconut, nuts, cocoa and vanilla in mixing bowl. In saucepan, cook sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil and cook for 1 minute.
Pour over mixture and stir well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and cool.
Serve as either candy or cookies. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute shallots, celery and mushrooms in melted margarine.
In another pot, combine soup and cheese and cook until cheese melts. Cook and chop broccoli separately.
You then combine all the ingredients and serve in a chafing dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with the juice from the pineapple and oranges. Cook until thick.
Allow to cool.
Mix the fruit cocktail, bananas, oranges, pineapple and marshmallows.
Add the pudding and stir.
Lay the cherries on top.
Store in the refrigerator 1 hour.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix all together in a large pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt all ingredients in double boiler.
Stir until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Refrigerate in glass jars.
Makes 1 quart.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°
for 1/2 hour.

title: tofu loaf with mushroom gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all loaf ingredients, except parsley, and stir lightly with a fork to blend.
Oil an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch glass loaf pan.
Pat the tofu mixture into the baking dish.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Garnish with parsley.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Set oven at 350° and grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Blend butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and blend.
Sift flour and cocoa together.
Add to batter and blend well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour batter into greased pan and bake 30 minutes, until tested done.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: vegetarian chopped liver
directions: Preheat broiler.
Peel and slice eggplant 1/2-inch (1.5 cm) thick.
Place eggplant on a nonstick baking sheet and broil on both sides until tender, about 10 minutes on each side.
Coarsely chop and set aside.

title: pumpkin-chocolate nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in angel food pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Combine water and apple juice in saucepan.
Add Kool-Aid, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Mix well and bring just to a boil. Serve hot.
Garnish as desired.
Yields 16 servings.

title: corncob jelly(no kidding!)
directions: Add enough water to cobs to get 3 cups broth.
Boil.
Discard cobs.
Add sugar and boil 3 minutes.
Add 1 package Sure-Jell. Boil 3 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and top with melted paraffin.
The jelly tastes like apple jelly and has slight pink color.

title: cheesy spinach bites
directions: Saute garlic in oil in a skillet. Add spinach and cook until spinach wilts. Remove from heat and add Italian seasoning and cheese; mix well. Place mixture on each cracker and bake for 5 to 7 minutes at 375°.

title: hero burger
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, tomatoes and cheese. Spread evenly over 1 loaf of French bread or 6 hot dog buns, split and toasted.
Cover edges completely.
Broil about 4 inches from heat for 12 minutes, then top with slices of tomatoes and sliced cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream cone pie
directions: Place the sugar cones in a plastic bag and crush into small pieces with a rolling pin. Mix crushed cones with pecans in a medium bowl; set aside. Put the chocolate chips and butter in a small heavy saucepan and melt, stirring occasionally over low heat. Pour over cone mixture; mix well. Press one third of the mixture evenly over the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Spread half of the ice cream over crust mixture. Sprinkle another third of the crumbs over ice cream and spread remaining ice cream over crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top of pie and press down crumbs with the back of a spoon. Cover and freeze for several
hours or until firm.
Pie may be kept frozen for up to a month.

title: wiener snitzel a la holstein
directions: Season the veal chops with salt and pepper. Season the flour with salt and pepper. Season the egg wash with salt and pepper. Season the bread crumbs with salt and pepper. Dredge the veal slices in the flour. Dip each slice in the egg wash, letting the excess drip off.
Finally, dredge the chops in the seasoned bread crumbs, coating evenly.

title: venison beer burgers
directions: 1. Break bread into small pieces and place in bowl. Pour beer over bread.
2. Once the beer is soaked up in the bread, add ground
meat, onion, sage, salt, and pepper. Mix well.
3. Form into patties and refrigerate 1 hour to allow
flavors to blend. Grill until done.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Crush cookies and mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours.
If using a fresh pineapple, hollow out and pour dip in pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight (do not use extract).

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place fruit in 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Mix sugar, oats, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle topping over filling. Bake in 375° oven 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients about 4 minutes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Mash cooked turnips.
Add 1/2 cup crumbs, beaten egg, cream, salt and sugar.
Mix together.
Add milk gradually.
Place in a greased baking dish and cover with remaining crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: sue's peanut butter roll
directions: Use a candy thermometer.

title: sauerkraut and rice bake
directions: Combine in casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May add pork chops or Polish sausage for a one dish meal.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine milk, water and soup. Stir or whisk.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased 3-quart casserole.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Stir once, halfway through baking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grangers doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together, liquids first.
Then add dry ingredients.
Roll out and cut with a doughnut cutter.
Drop into hot grease until golden brown.
Flip over and brown other side. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: pineapple orange creme frozen dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumb mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture in ungreased baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
In mixer bowl, beat dry milk, orange juice and egg white on high speed for 3 minutes.
Add lemon juice; beat 3 minutes.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Freeze for at least 8 hours.
Makes 9 servings.

title: california chicken
directions: Cook carrots and potatoes and drain.
Add peas and tuna. Cover with Cream Sauce.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mary lankford's salad dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Serve over green salad of your choice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter, then stir in flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and salt.
Stir in cream corn and milk.
Bake in casserole at 375° until firm and lightly browned.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: In heavy medium saucepan, combine sugar, unflavored gelatin, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Let stand one minute.
Over low heat cook and stir constantly until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pumpkin mix well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put your shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Pour your cup of scalded milk in the mixture and melt shortening.
Blend sugar. While this is cooling, combine the package of yeast and 1/2 cup of hot water.
Let dissolve and set.
When your milk mixture is cooled to lukewarm, add 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon salt and the yeast. Add 1 cup of flour and mix.
Add remaining flour until you have your dough where you can handle it.
Make into rolls.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: radish and cream cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, celery salt, paprika and Worcestershire sauce together, until smooth.
Stir in onion and radishes.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with fresh vegetables:
celery, carrots, cauliflower, broccoli, etc.

title: clam chowder soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
In boiler, add water, chicken broth and margarine.
Chop garlic and add to mixture.
Chop onion and add to mixture with salt and pepper.
Cook potatoes until they are all to pieces.
Don't let liquid cook lower than 2 inches above potatoes.
After potatoes are cooked, mix cornstarch with milk and add to soup.
Don't add clams until the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Enjoy.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add corn, water, tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Stir up rice, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes to cook rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mandel bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the eggs, oil and lemon juice; beat well.
Add the remaining ingredients including chocolate chips and walnuts, if desired.
Shape into long strips and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes. When golden brown, remove from the oven and cut at an angle while still hot.
Return to the cookie sheet and toast each side under the broiler.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Set jar of syrup in pan of boiling water on stove to melt. Combine pudding mix with milk in mixer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and mix until blended.
Layer the following in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan:
whole graham crackers, half pudding mixture, whole graham crackers, remaining pudding mixture and whole graham crackers.
Pour syrup over top.
Chill.

title: delicious dressing
directions: Mix the corn bread, biscuits, toasted loaf bread, salt, pepper, sage, eggs and onion in a large bowl; refrigerate overnight.
Boil the turkey neck, gizzard, liver and heart together; add some of this broth to the dressing when ready to cook.
Also add mayonnaise, milk, turkey drippings and, if mixture needs to be more moist, add a little water.
Pour into a large baking pan; dot with margarine.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 450°.
Dressing is done when a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: super duper bean pot
directions: Fry onions and garlic in fat until soft, not brown.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: super sloppy joes
directions: Place onion and ground beef in a large, microwave-safe bowl. Mix well.
Cook on High 4 minutes or until beef is brown.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Add soup and seasoning mix, mix well.
Cover. Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until hot.
Place one open hamburger bun on each plate.
Top with equal amounts of meat mixture.
Serves 4.

title: potato and cabbage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until half soft.
Peel skins and cut in 1/4 inch slices; set on side.
Melt margarine in frying pan.
Saute cabbage and onions until soft.
Add sliced potatoes, mix well.
Sprinkle with garlic to taste (a lot).
Lay half of cabbage/potato mixture in big casserole dish.
Sprinkle cup of cheese over mixture. Spread other half of cabbage/potato mixture on top of cheese.
In small pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter, add 1/4 cup flour and mix until bubbles.
Slowly add chicken broth, mixing well.
When thick, pour over cabbage/potato mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coleslaw souffle salad
directions: In a bowl dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in mayonnaise, vinegar, cold water and salt.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix white cake mix according to package directions and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is warm, poke holes in cake with meat fork.

title: butter brickle brownies
directions: Bake at 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips last. Bake in 9 x 12-inch cake pan that has been lightly greased and floured.

title: easy company cake
directions: Cook cake as directed. When cool, slice in rounds and fill with pudding, Stack cake rounds, filling with pudding. Cover with cool whip and sprinkle with nuts on top. Store in refrigerator.

title: basic cream filling
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together; add enough milk to moisten.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Add rest of milk and butter. Cook in saucepan over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly to keep from sticking or scorching.
Cool and add vanilla.
Save egg whites for meringue.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Combine the sugar, water, salt and corn syrup in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Bring to a boil in microwave oven, about 3 minutes. Stir and add peanuts.
Cook 9 to 11 minutes more, or until soft-ball stage (234°) is reached.
Remove from microwave oven and add margarine, vanilla and food coloring.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Drop by the spoonful or pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: cheese spread
directions: Grind ingredients together and spread on crackers.

title: libby's sour cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and margarine in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy (1 minute).
Add sour cream, eggs and vanilla; continue beating until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes).

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Use to marinate or for a sauce.
(Tastes like Brooks chicken.)

title: pickled carrots
directions: Peel carrots.
Cut to 4-inches long and 1/4-inch thick.
Tie pickling spice in cheesecloth to make a small bag.

title: tuscan fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into equal sizes.
Put into a casserole and sprinkle with parsley and lemon juice. Pour on olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
Turn chichen in marinade and let stand in refrigerator for about 2 hours.

title: buttermilk drumsticks
directions: Place chicken in a 9-inch square baking dish; pour buttermilk over meat.
Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and onion powder in a plastic bag.
Add chicken to bag, close tight and shake to coat.
Heat 1 inch oil in a large skillet to 325°; add chicken and cook about 10 minutes.
Turn once, cover, reduce heat and cook 20 minutes, turning often.
Remove cover and cook 3 more minutes.
Drain chicken on paper towels.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: hamburger pasties pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
In large bowl, combine all remaining ingredients except pie crusts.
Mix well.
Add hamburger and onion.
Mix. Pour into one pie crust.
Top with second pie crust.
Pinch edges.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Shape into ball; roll in nuts and parsley.
Chill; serve with crackers.

title: pink divinity
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water until it reaches hard boil stage, 252°.
Stir occasionally while cooking.
Beat egg whites and add jello slowly; continue beating until forms a peak.
Add cooked syrup slowly to egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Add nuts and cherries.
Drop onto wax paper.
To make green divinity, use same recipe only use lime jello.
Very pretty - a real Christmas favorite.

title: dragon tail soup
directions: In a large pot, put potatoes, sausage, celery and onions and cover with water. Cook on medium heat for 1 hour. Add the soups and stir well. Cook for 1 hour. Serve with warm bread and butter.

title: s'more cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, graham cracker crumbs, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture, beating until blended.
Press half of dough into pan.
Arrange chocolate bars over dough, breaking as needed to fit.
Spread with marshmallow cream.
Spread remaining dough over marshmallow.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken; salt.
Add basil and cornflakes together.
Roll chicken in butter, then in basil and cornflakes.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: breakfast "garbage"
directions: Fry potatoes in skillet with 2 tablespoon oil.
After potatoes are brown, add bologna; let bologna brown.
Add green pepper; salt and pepper to taste.
Scramble eggs and add to potato mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and flavoring and beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5-inch) pans for 1 hour at 350°.
If desired, add 1/2 cup of crushed pineapple.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Break up frozen hash brown potatoes. Mix soup, sour cream and cheese. Stir in potatoes. Add onions, salt and pepper. Mix margarine with Rice Chex. Put potato mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with Rice Chex. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and add cream, nutmeg and raisins.
Pour into large, greased casserole dish.
Top with butter, brown sugar and marshmallows.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: yum yum
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine. Mix well. Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, dessert topping mix and milk. Spread half of cream mixture in 9 x 13 dish. Add 1/2 cream cheese mixture. Spread on both cans of pie filling. Add remaining cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining crumbs. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Cream together until light and fluffy the butter or margarine and sugar.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir milk in slowly. Pour into well chilled, uncooked crust and bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes or until firm.
Serve slightly warm.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Put 2 pork chops in bottom; salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour.
Cover with a layer of potatoes, sliced about 1/4-inch thick.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used, ending with a layer of potatoes on top. Salt and pepper every layer of pork chops.
Cover with milk to top of mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until meat is tender and potatoes are done, approximately 1 hour.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in large microwavable bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk until well blended.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.

title: turtle cake
directions: Follow cake recipe.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt caramels with evaporated milk.
While cake is hot, pour caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and 1 cup nuts. Pour remaining batter on top and cover with 1 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: brunch casserole #1
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish and place bread, buttered side down, in dish.
Cook sausage; drain off excess fat, then crumble over bread slices.
Beat eggs and sour cream.
Pour over sausage; sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Uncover and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or in 325° oven if a glass pan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put potatoes in bottom of pan, then layer spaghetti sauce, green beans or other favorite vegetable, then cheese.
Continue to layer. Top layer should be potatoes with cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: d-lish chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat chicken with sour cream.
Dredge in stuffing mix.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.
Baste with mixture of melted butter and vermouth every 15 minutes while baking.
Makes chicken special.

title: quick and easy hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add soup.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Do not allow to boil.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1 teaspoon of mixture per cup of hot water.
Sprinkle in "red hots" (candy) if desired.

title: applesauce cake(low cholesterol)
directions: Combine sugar and oil
in
mixing
bowl.
Add
soda
to applesauce.
Combine sugar and
oil.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Add raisins
and nuts.
Sift together flour, cocoa, cinnamon, cloves and allspice
and add to first mixture.
Beat at medium speed for 2	minutes.
Pour	batter	in
greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake
at
325° for 70 minutes.
Let cool in pan, then remove to cake plate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, oleo, syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes (or cook in microwave and boil 3 minutes).
Stir soda in well until mixture is a very light brown.
Spray two large 9 x 13-inch cake pans with Pam.
Divide popcorn between two pans and pour caramel mixture over popcorn and stir (or put popcorn in large grocery sack), pour caramel over and shake
until coated.
Cook in microwave for three minutes, turning sack after each minute. Place in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes or it will burn.
Nuts can be added before baking.
Store in airtight container.

title: grandma's german sauerkraut
directions: Put all ingredients except butter and flour into pot.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Melt butter; stir in flour, then stir into sauerkraut mixture.
Remove from heat and keep covered 5 minutes.

title: old fashioned skillet dinner
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown onions, seasonings and beef. Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches or 3 loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake until a wooden toothpick comes out clean, about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions and set aside.
Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar.
By hand, add cool whip and pudding to butter mixture.
In the bottom of a bowl or 13 x 9-inch cake pan, place some vanilla wafers, then a layer of bananas, then pudding mixture.
Continue to layer, then refrigerate.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Add cooked broccoli and reduce heat, add milk and cheese chunks, stir until melted and season with pepper.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: sun-maid raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream shortening with sugar; then add beaten eggs and milk.
Combine with oatmeal and raisins; mix well.
Add flour sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon. Beat thoroughly.
Drop onto greased pans and bake about 12 minutes in a moderate oven (350° to 375°).
Yields 3 dozen.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 13 x 9 x 2 1/4 pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: n. c. coastal seafood casserole
directions: Melt the cream cheese and 1 stick butter or margarine using a double boiler or microwave.
Saute shrimp, onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons butter. Add to the first mixture.
Add soup, mushrooms, seasonings, crab meat and rice.
Mix well and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with mixture of cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly. Cool slightly and serve.

title: rhubarb dessert(delicious)
directions: Mix this like a pie crust.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar together.
Then add strawberries, eggs, Crisco oil and nuts.
Mix well and pour into 2 large or 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Store in refrigerator well wrapped.
The flavor improves the longer it is stored.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a large baking dish.
Pour extra ketchup on top and spread over meat loaf.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Blend and put in oven proof dish. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: turkey rolls italiano
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Heat olive oil and saute onion, pepper and garlic.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add to olive mixture and toss.
Pound turkey slices flat.
Spread mixture over top of each slice.
Roll tightly and secure with toothpicks.
Cover and chill.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie batter in well greased pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: weight watchers parmesan fried chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, pepper and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
Roll chicken pieces first in the dressing, then in crumb mixture.
Place in a baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
I find that the crumb mixture is ample to coat 6 to 8 pieces of chicken, especially if they are small.
I have used thighs in place of breasts and it also is a good coating for pork chops or fish (decrease the cooking time for fish).
I use the Pepperidge Farm herb seasoned stuffing instead of bread crumbs.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve first 4 ingredients in hot water and cool until syrupy.
Whip evaporated milk.
Fold 2 mixtures together.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger-rice skillet
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink; drain. Stir in tomato and green chiles and next 4 ingredients. Cook, covered, over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Uncover and cook 15 more minutes; remove from heat. Sprinkle lettuce and next 5 ingredients over hamburger mixture. Stand tortilla chips around edge of skillet. Serve with chips and salsa. Yield: 6 servings.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: In plastic bag, mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Shake potato chunks in mixture to coat.
Melt margarine in baking dish. Put coated potatoes in butter in 1 layer.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, turning once during cooking.

title: cheese sausage biscuits
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature while mixing together. Roll into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza soup
directions: Brown sausage, onion, pepper and garlic.
Add rest of ingredients except macaroni and cheese.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Add macaroni; cook 20 minutes.
Serve with cheese on top.

title: baked eggs
directions: Cook sausage in frying pan and drain off grease.
In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add milk, mustard, cubed bread, cheese and sausage. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture into it. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Remove cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Let sit a few minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make paste of vinegar and cocoa.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vinegar and cocoa mixture.
Add flour, soda and salt together with milk, vanilla and coloring.
Makes 3 layers.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese sandwich spread
directions: Mix all together.
Put on warm heat while mixing; do not boil. Pimento can be optional. Good on dark bread.

title: orange mandarin cake
directions: For icing, mix well instant vanilla pudding mix, Cool Whip and crushed pineapple. Set aside until cake has cooled.

For cake, mix Duncan Hines cake mix, mandarin oranges, oil, and eggs. Bake at 325° in three layers for 20 minutes. When cake has cooled remove from cake pans and ice cake making a three-layer cake. Put in refrigerator over night.

title: frozen cranberry banana salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a bowl; set pineapple aside.
Add sliced bananas to pineapple juice.
In a large bowl, combine cranberry juice and sugar.
Remove bananas, discarding juice and add to cranberry mixture.
Stir in pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts. Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Freeze until solid.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in a saucepan until onion is soft.
Blend in the flour, salt and garlic salt.
Add milk and soy sauce and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in the chicken. Drain the water chestnuts.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Place layers of noodles and chicken mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, beginning and ending with noodles.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, 1 1/2 cups of sugar and eggs.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan.
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 12 dozen.

title: supreme beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar and garlic to taste.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Cook noodles and drain. Blend sour cream and cream cheese with noodles. In a 3-quart casserole dish, layer meat sauce, noodles and grated cheese. Top with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: mrs. eunice's giblet gravy
directions: Melt butter and then add enough flour to thicken. Mix well and add broth, 1 can at a time. Stir each can in well. Add chopped giblets and chopped eggs. Let simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste. Add flour or broth as needed for your desired thickness.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, bananas, raisins and nuts; mix with salad dressing and serve over lettuce and pineapple ring.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork and pour Kahlua over brownies.
Set aside.
Whip up chocolate mouse according to package directions. Break up half of the brownies and place in the bottom of a glass bowl.
Cover with half of the mousse; layer with half of the candy, then add half of the whipped topping.
Repeat layers.

title: ground beef vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef, onion and bay leaf; drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: summer tomato salad
directions: Combine vegetables and cheese.
Squeeze juice from lemon over vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cool carrots
directions: Pare carrots and slice.
Cook in salted water 10 minutes only. Drain and let cool.
Mix other ingredients and cook 5 minutes. Pour over carrots.
Put in container; refrigerate.
Serve cold. Will keep for days.

title: basic cream sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Remove pan from fire and add flour and salt, slowly add milk.
Return to fire.
Bring to boil for one minute.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with apples. Turn into pastry and dot with butter. Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in crust and sprinkle with sugar. Cover edges of crust with aluminum foil. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: blueberry layered dessert
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions, then add sugar and cream cheese; mix well.
Place 1/2 of the graham cracker crumbs in large dish.
Then, layer 1/2 the whipped cream, the can of pie filling and the other 1/2 of the whipped cream; put remaining graham crackers on top.
Refrigerate.

title: cream of butternut squash and leek soup
directions: Clean, peel, deseed and cut squash into 1-inch pieces.
Melt butter in a heavy large pan over medium-high heat.
Add leeks and stir 4 minutes.
Add squash and stir to coat with butter.
Mix in stock, thyme and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until squash is tender, about 40 minutes.
Puree soup in batches in processor or blender.
Return to large pan.
Mix in cream and milk.
Reheat soup over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add freshly ground pepper.
Ladle soup into bowls.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Garnish with optional chopped chives or parsley. Serve and enjoy!!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Put 1 slice cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Combine soup and water and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over soup mixture.
Pour melted butter on top of stuffing mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, paprika, sesame seeds, poppy seeds to make dressing. Toss spinach and strawberries. The dressing can be made the day before. Stir the dressing as you serve on the salad.

title: fudge souffl
directions: Whisk the cocoa powder, powdered sugar and milk in the top of a double boiler over boiling water until smooth. Add the chocolate chips and stir until the chips are melted. Stir and lower the heat to a simmer.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Pour 1/2 macaroni
into
a
1/2 quart greased baking dish. Put slices
of Velveeta on macaroni.
Pour in remainder of macaroni and
put
sliced
Cheddar
on top.
Mix margarine, eggs, milk and
water and pour over layered macaroni.
Bake at 375° for 25 to
minutes
until
cheese
on top is browned. (For thinner sauce, add more liquid; for thicker sauce, reduce liquid.)

title: black bottom teacakes
directions: Blend and set aside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini in thin slices. Butter casserole dish and spread with corn flakes cereal. Layer zucchini. Top with slices of tomato. Sprinkle with minced onion, parsley, basil and oregano. Dot with butter and cover with grated cheese. Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin broccoli toss
directions: Toss first 4 ingredients together.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over the first ingredients.
Toss to coat thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate "prayer" bars
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter. Add the cocoa, 1/2 cup powdered sugar, nuts, coconut, egg, vanilla and crushed graham crackers. Mix well and press down in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: my favorite recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased casserole for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: 3 vegetable latkes
directions: In a bowl, combine eggs, shredded vegetables, parsley, salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in matzo meal.
Shape into flat cakes, using 1 to 2 tablespoons mixture for each.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with milk.
Combine with ground beef, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into balls.
Place in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients to make barbecue sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: jello cream cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and cool with 6 or 7 ice cubes until partially set.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bake one of the pie crusts in a dish.
Cut chicken up; then add the soups and Veg-All.
Cover with other pie crust.
Cook on 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown on top.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water or juice into Jell-O in large bowl 3 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water about 15 seconds.
Cut into decorative shapes with cookie cutters all the way through the Jell-O.
Lift from pan. Makes about 24 pieces.

title: big bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add soda to buttermilk and add and mix like biscuit dough.
Roll out on floured board to about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into strips and twist and hook ends together.
Fry in deep hot fat.
We dip ours in syrup and eat; it is like the bread used for elephant ears.

title: "jennie's" half sour pickles
directions: Brine:
Boil water, vinegar and salt 5 to 10 minutes; allow to cool to lukewarm.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together in order given. Bake in bread pan at 350° until done.

title: no cook christmas cookies
directions: Mix well and shape into balls, about the size of a walnut. Roll in sugar and refrigerate.

title: herb chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter.
Combine cornflake crumbs and herbs.
Roll buttered chicken in crumb mixture to coat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in shallow baking pan.
Do not crowd.

title: shrimp salad
directions: If canned shrimp are
used, soak them in cold water for 2 minutes.
Drain them and moisten with lemon juice.	Then add celery, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Garnish the salad with the
eggs,
olives and watercress.
Serve on tomato slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Fry first 3 ingredients and drain.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix.
Spread on party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Can be frozen ahead of time.

title: cream cheese cake squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Dissolve the cornstarch in 1 cup of milk.
Heat the remaining milk and add cornstarch, stirring constantly.
Add the well beaten egg yolks and sugar.
Stir constantly and cook over low heat forever, about 45 minutes, until the mixture coats a metal spoon. After cooking, add melted chocolate and stir in.
Cool several hours or overnight in refrigerator, if possible.
When ready to freeze, beat the egg whites, salt and vanilla to a froth and add to the chilled mixture.
Stir in cream and pour into 5-quart freezer; add additional milk if needed to fill line.
Freeze in hand or electric ice cream freezer.
Pack down for an hour or so.
Enjoy.

title: polynesian rice
directions: Stir-fry strips of beef in 2 tablespoons cooking oil in Dutch oven.
When done, remove to a bowl.
If needed, add more oil to Dutch oven to stir-fry tomatoes, green pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Season with soy sauce, hot pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Add stir-fried beef and 1 can of Chinese vegetables. Thicken sauce with cornstarch that has been blended with 2 tablespoons water.
Serve over cooked instant rice.

title: 15 bean lowfat soup
directions: Cover the beans with water and allow to soak overnight or for several hours.
Drain.
Cover with water again and add onions, sausage, bouillon granules, bay leaves, tomatoes, salt, and Worcestershire.
Cook until beans are tender.
It may be necessary to add a little water during cooking.
Remove bay leaves.
Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.
About 10 servings.

title: griddle buster pear cake
directions: Melt butter and add to cake mix.
Mix to form a ball.
Take 3/4 of ball and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add pears that have been cut into small pieces.
Sprinkle cinnamon over pears.
Mix eggs, softened cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour over pears.
Crumble rest of cake mix on top.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: caribbean beans and rice
directions: Place all ingredients except for peas in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low to medium and simmer, 20 to 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Mix in peas.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes and serve.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Mix egg, applesauce and vanilla and let sit.
Cream together sugar and Spry.
Add cocoa, flour and baking soda to sugar and Spry and blend.
Mix well with wet ingredients.
Bake in pan with hole at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Frost with white sauce icing.

title: super macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Rinse in cold water to cool quickly. Combine all other ingredients in macaroni and mix well.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cornmeal batter rolls
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 3/4 cup of the flour, the cornmeal, yeast and baking powder.
Heat and stir together milk, shortening, sugar and salt just until warm (115° to 120°) until shortening almost melts.
Add to dry ingredients in mixer bowl; add egg.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
At low speed, beat in remaining flour 2 minutes or until smooth.
To mix and bake the same day, let batter rise 1 hour; drop into muffin pans and let rise 45 minutes.

title: buttered noodles
directions: Place the water, eggs, flour and salt in the bowl of an electric mixer.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes or until batter is smooth and some bubbles start to appear.
Let the batter rest at room temperature for 30 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add sliced or chopped onions.
Add mushrooms.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce and simmer 15 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain; combine eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Stir in margarine, cheese and seasoning.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, core and grind pears.
Weigh after grinding.
Add sugar, no water required.
Cook until pears are tender and syrup thickens.
Add pineapple and honey and cook until thick.
Seal while hot.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut chicken livers in
half.
Slice
water chestnuts in 1/3. Marinate chicken livers
and water chestnuts in teriyaki sauce for 3 to 4
hours.
Keep refrigerated.	Drain off sauce. Cut bacon
Wrap bacon around chicken liver and water chestnut. Secure.
Roll
in brown sugar (optional).
Broil or bake at 500° until done.
Turn occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: fruit stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut
tops
off
tomatoes.
Gently
scoop
out pulp from centers,
leaving
a 1/4-inch thick shell.
(Pulp can be saved for later
use in soups and stews.) Turn shells upside down to drain. Sprinkle
shells
with
salt;
set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream cottage cheese and cream cheese together.
Stir in apple,
orange, nuts and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Stuff tomatoes 1/3 to
1/2 cup full. Garnish
with
orange
sections
and
nuts. Chill.
(This recipe is unusual but good.)

title: apple salad
directions: In a bowl, mix all the ingredients together.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 2.

title: four cheese lasagna
directions: Brown beef, sausage, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Combine Ricotta, 3 cups Mozzarella, 1 cup grated cheese and eggs in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly and set aside.
Spread one cup meat sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer 4 noodles, cheese mixture and meat sauce. Repeat layering once, conserving 1 cup meat sauce.
Top with remaining 4 noodles and remaining 1/4 cup grated Parmesan and Romano cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Remove foil.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and return to oven until cheese melts.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: batter-fried chicken(excellent with shrimp too!)
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Add beer, stirring with wire whisk until smooth. Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: In large bowl, mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, bread crumbs and egg.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, firmly shape mixture into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove loaf from oven and pour off fat.

title: double dutch chocolate treat
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Mix dry cake mix in pudding until blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch can pan (greased).
Sprinkle chocolate bits and nuts over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions; drain.
In a large pot, saute onion in butter until done.
Add prepared broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Simmer until cheese melts and blended into soup.
Serves 6.

title: judy's cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll into a ball.
Place in refrigerator until firm. Roll in pecans.

title: taco casserole
directions: Prepare ground beef according to taco seasoning mix package instructions.

Pour refried beans into a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly in bottom of pan; spread chopped olives evenly over beans. Mix salsa with ground beef; simmer approximately 15 minutes. Spread over beans and olives.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture; add tomatoes, lettuce and tortilla chips.
Use sour cream as desired.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Add flour and salt, alternating with milk. Add food coloring and vanilla. Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of rice in shallow casserole dish.
Add ham, 2/3 of cheese and eggs.
Add remaining rice.
Mix mushroom soup and chicken broth together.
Pour over casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all in bowl and pour in shell.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: frosty chocolate shake
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over 1/4 cup milk (reserving 1/4 cup).
Let stand 1 minute, then stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.

title: spicy pineapple barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a 1-quart saucepan and put over low heat until melted.
Brush over ribs or kabobs.
Makes 1 cup.

title: saucy baked pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops and heat the fat in skillet (or use nonstick spray). When the fat has melted, remove trimmings and add pork chops. Brown chops in pan and season with salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Place chops in a casserole dish and pour mixture over them.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raspberry trifle
directions: Arrange 1/3 of sliced cake on the bottom of a trifle dish or large decorative bowl.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Place 1/3 more cake pieces around inside of bowl, using half of pudding.
Cover with remaining cake pieces.
Layer remaining pudding and raspberry mixture.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream and fresh raspberries.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit cup
directions: Combine nuts and fruit.
Put in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well, using hands. Beat eggs until foamy. Add to mixture. Blend well.
Use small baking cups.
Fill cups full. Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Pour undiluted soup over meat in pan.
Add drained mushrooms, sherry and onion.
Cover and bake at 275° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: aunt ellie's scones(english)
directions: In bowl, sift together first 5 ingredients.
Cut in butter until it resembles small peas.
Add fruit.
Stir in buttermilk, little by little, with the blade of a knife.
As soon as dough gathers, stop adding buttermilk.
Knead gently, only enough to form into 2-inch balls.
Roll out on lightly floured board into 1/2-inch thick rounds and into pie slice wedges.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with milk.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for about 20 minutes.
Split, butter and serve with jam.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 12 (3 x 2-inch) loose rolls.
Remove 12 or more leaves from cabbage, enough to cover 12 meat rolls.
Parboil cabbage leaves in a small amount of water until leaves wilt.
Wrap each meat ball in a leaf of cabbage.
Put rolls in a tall baking casserole and cover with tomato juice.
Sprinkle with a little pepper and salt and cover tightly.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
More tomato juice can be added during baking.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in a medium-size salad bowl as follows:
1st Layer: lettuce, torn in pieces. 2nd Layer:
celery. 3rd Layer:
onion. Pour sour cream and sugar mixture over above. 4th Layer:
bacon. Pour mayonnaise and vinegar mixture over the above and sprinkle cheese over salad.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, margarine, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours. Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in flour.
Bake until light brown, 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Make balls small.
Spread quite a bit.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Peel and core apples and cut into slices. Boil apples until tender. Drain and add sugar to taste and butter. Continue to cook until thick, stirring often. After it cools, put into refrigerator.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all together, except drippings.
Put drippings in pan and heat.
Add to mixture and bake at 400° until done.
(We triple the recipe in the Tullie kitchen and cook in a 10-inch spider pan.
Do not triple salt if you use drippings.)

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the cheese.
Beat in syrup.
Add lemon juice and bananas.
Stir in pineapple, strawberries, dates and pecans.
Fold in the whipped cream. Line muffin baking pan with paper bake cups. Fill with salad.
Freeze until firm.
Store in plastic bag in freezer.
Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: caramels
directions: Combine all except heavy cream and vanilla.
Let all sugars dissolve.
Bring to boil, then add the heavy cream.
Cook to a chewy stage when a little is tested in water, then add vanilla. Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch square pan. Cool; cut in small squares and wrap in waxed paper.
Use a heavy pan for cooking.

title: martha washington balls(bonbons)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Will be very stiff.
Make into bite size balls.
Chill until firm.
Use a toothpick to dip into chocolate mix.
Remove toothpick.
Chill again.

title: jessie's lima beans with mushrooms and celery
directions: Cook lima beans according to package directions.
Quickly rinse mushrooms and gently pat dry with paper towel.
Cut stems even with mushroom caps.
Slice vertically.

title: chicken 'n stuffing casserole
directions: Skin chicken and place in large baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and cream.
Pour over cheese.
Top with stuffing mix and dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.

title: sour cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls; roll each ball in coconut.
These can be frozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough in pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled cookie.
Top with sliced fruits of your choice.
Chill before serving.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook together brown sugar, white sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk until thick; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: crabmeat and shrimp plate
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on a 9 or 10-inch plate.
Cover with 1/2 or 3/4 bottle of seafood cocktail sauce.
Sprinkle shrimp and crabmeat over sauce.
You can sprinkle shredded cheese on top and chill.
Serve with a knife or spread on Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash apples; quarter, removing core.
Cook with peeling and 4 to 6 cups water.
Stir and cook down until tender.
Press through a colander or sieve.
Return to pot and sweeten to taste.
Add the red hots and cloves.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Seal in jars. Makes about 15 quarts.
I usually only make 1/2 of the recipe.

title: devil's food cupcakes
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Add Crisco; pour in water, vanilla and 2 tablespoons buttermilk.
Mix with mixer at low speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining buttermilk, egg and egg yolk; mix well.
Pour into pan for cupcakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten and fit together rolls in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until crust is lightly brown.

title: zucchini sweet relish
directions: Grind and let stand overnight: onions, zucchini and salt. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain for 1 hour.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes and seal in hot cans.

title: night before french toast
directions: Use extra butter to grease a 15 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices and arrange in one layer in bottom of pan.

title: ronnie's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form meatballs and fry in oil until brown.

title: popa's chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in soup pot.
Cover with water and add bouillon cubes, 1 teaspoon pepper and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
Cook 1 hour or until chicken pulls away from bones.
Remove chicken, de-skin and debone.
Set aside.
Make meatballs about 1-inch with chopped meat, 1 teaspoon pepper and 1 teaspoon nutmeg mixed into meat.
Put into broth and cook.
Chop celery, carrots, scallions and parsley.
Add to broth.
Put chicken into broth.
Add noodles.
Cook until noodles are done and vegetables are soft.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Chill pie filling and pineapple.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into individual serving dishes, if desired, or one large dish.
Chill 30 minutes.
Garnish with sugar wafer cookies.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: skillet franks-n-noodles
directions: Cut franks in half diagonally.
In skillet, brown franks and cook onion with basil and margarine until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Stir now and then.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add rest of ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 300°.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Set aside 1 cup Mozzarella for topping. Combine Ricotta, remaining 3 cups Mozzarella and egg in a bowl. Add spinach. Spread 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce over bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Place 5 dry noodles over this in a single layer, 4 lengthways and 1 crossways. The crossways one will be too long, so break off the end to make it fit. Place half of cheese mixture on top of the noodles. Pour another 3/4 cup of sauce over cheese mixture; lay remaining noodles on top of sauce. Top with remaining cheese mixture. Pour remaining sauce over all and finally, top with the 1 cup reserved Mozzarella. The uncooked dish can sit all day or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Layer cabbage, pepper rings and onion rings in large bowl and sprinkle cup of sugar on top.
Mix mustard, 2 teaspoons sugar, celery seed, vinegar, salad oil and salt.
Bring to full boil and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours.

title: black bean wraps
directions: Beat cream cheese, cheese, sour cream and salt at medium speed with an electric mixer until thoroughly blended.
Set cheese mixture aside.
Process beans and salsa in a food processor until smooth. Spread bean mixture evenly over tortillas; top each evenly with cheese mixture, spinach, peppers and olives.
Roll tortillas tightly (can wrap in plastic and chill if desired).
Heat in oven at 350° until warm.

title: stir-fried broccoli slices
directions: Spray a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Combine ingredients in the skillet over heat.
Cover and cook 2 minutes; remove cover.
Cook and stir until most of the liquid evaporates. (Add a splash of soy sauce, if desired.)
Makes 4 servings, under 50 calories each.

title: sweet potato and pineapple casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mash sweet potatoes and beat until smooth. Stir in brown sugar and pineapple. Pour into 1 qt.
casserole. Bake 20 minutes.
Arrange marshmallows over potatoes and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: pie
directions: Melt Jell-O in 1/4 cup of warm water. Then blend the yogurt into the Jell-O. Then you blend in the Cool Whip. Put into the crust and let chill. That's it!
ENJOY.

title: banana trifle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cubes to cold water to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin; stir until slightly thickened. Stir in bananas and strawberries.
Place cake cubes in large serving bowl; sprinkle with orange juice.
Spoon gelatin mixture over cake.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Prepare pudding mix with 1 1/2 cups milk as directed on package.
Let stand a few minutes to thicken.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon over gelatin.
Chill.

title: meat pops(snack for parties)
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese and milk, stirring with wooden spoon until the cream cheese is smooth enough to spread. Using spatula, spread each slice of lunch meat with the cream cheese mixture.
Roll a meat slice diagonally around each pretzel stick near one end.

title: fruitcake cookie
directions: Combine cherries, pineapple, pitted dates and flour, then add the pecans, coconut and sweetened condensed milk. Mix well. Roll in 1-inch balls. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
After thoroughly mixed, form into ball.
Roll cheese ball in chopped pecans.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter; add 1 1/2 cups sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually and mix. Chill in refrigerator.
Mold dough into small balls and roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.
Store in covered container.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add water and chicken seasoning; bring to a boil.
In bottom of casserole, put rice, chicken and mushroom soup.
Put sauteed onion and celery on top. Bake for 1 hour and 50 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: point molate punch
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Bring to boil and cool.
Mix orange juice, pineapple juice and bananas.
Mix with sugar-water.
Freeze in quart containers.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Press firmly into bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Stir in Amaretto.
Pour over crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Combine the sour cream, sugar and Amaretto, stirring well.
Spoon over cheesecake.
Bake at 500° for 5 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature, then refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Garish with grated chocolate and almonds.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Whisk
together the ingredients.
