Chill and use on cole slaw or lettuce salad.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: opal's rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water; set aside.
Mix buttermilk, shortening and sugar.
Add yeast.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Pour onto greased surface and knead 6 to 8 minutes.
Put into large greased bowl; turn to grease both sides.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, pinch out rolls into desired shape.
Put in greased pan.
Let raise 2 to 3 hours.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 420° until golden brown.
Dough will keep in the refrigerator for 1 week.
Good while hot with butter.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and mix.
Add pineapple, milk and potatoes; mix and pour into a buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: best all-american brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Coat a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Melt the butter and let cool.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.

title: sausage pecan dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery tops in butter.
Cook sausage in separate skillet.
Add salt, pepper and thyme to bread crumbs. Add crumb mixture to skillet with vegetables.
Drain sausage.
Add sausage and broth to vegetable mixture.
Add more melted butter if needed.
Taste for seasoning.
Add pecans.
Makes enough stuffing for ten-pound bird.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, and eggs, and syrup. Sift all dry ingredients together. Add alternately with milk. Chill until stiff enough to roll on floured board. Cut with small glass or lid. Bake at 400° until golden brown. Yields 5 dozen.

title: paprikash potatoes
directions: In large skillet, brown onions in one tablespoon of butter. Remove from pan and set aside.
Slice potatoes like home fries. Place potatoes in skillet and add salt, pepper and loads of sweet paprika.
Add browned onions; cover with water and cook, covered, for about 25 minutes until well done.

title: mallow mint dessert
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the marshmallows and milk. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes or until marshmallows are melted. Stir until smooth. Cool to room temperature. Stir in the mint extract and food coloring. Fold in whipped cream.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, oil, apples and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with apple mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
This cake is delicious hot or served 2 days later.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for a few hours.
Serve cold.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water, then add 2 cups cold water.
Let the Jell-O thicken, then add pineapple, cream cheese and marshmallows.
Pour the mixture into a square dish and then cover and refrigerate until set.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: homemade butter
directions: You will need 1 quart jar with tight lid.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Flour and butter a long cake pan.
Spread chopped pecans on bottom of pan.
Spread coconut over pecans.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over top of coconut.

title: tasty dried beef casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender, about 5 minutes. Cut dried beef into small pieces; add to onion mixture and continue cooking until beef is slightly browned. Stir in soup, milk, pepper and paprika. Heat to boiling. Cook macaroni, using unsalted water. Drain, then rinse with cold water and drain again.
Combine macaroni with dried beef sauce. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Dice streak of lean and cook in large frying pan until brown and dry; remove from grease.
Cook chopped onions in grease until tender.
Add streak of lean and shrimp.
Stir until shrimp turn pink.
Add rice and stir well.
Add soy sauce and pepper. Add enough soy sauce to turn rice a rich dark brown.
Keep on simmer until ready to serve.

title: lemon pineapple punch
directions: Mix 14 c. water & 3 c. sugar in large pot and boil.
Then add jello, lemon juice, and pineapple juice, and stir.
Pour into gallon jugs and freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: eggs a la roro
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a pan.
Stir in a tablespoon of flour.
Add 1/2 cup of milk.
Add cheese.
Break eggs in a tablespoon of melted butter in a small Pyrex dish.
Pour sauce over eggs.
Bake at 350° until egg yellows are done and top is brown.

title: home baked potatoes
directions: Place 1/2 Potatoes in a greased 2 quart or 11 x 7 x 2 inch baking dish.
Top with Onions and other Potatoes.
Drizzle with Butter, sprinkle Cheese, Salt, Pepper and Garlic Powder.
Bake uncovered 450 for 25 - 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Feeds 4.

title: saucy chicken wings
directions: Discard tips of wings or use for soup stock.
In small saucepan, mix soy sauce, sugar, garlic, pineapple or orange juice. Stir thoroughly, then add molasses, lemon juice, ginger and dry mustard.
Heat to nearly boiling.
Arrange wings in oven dish; pour mixture over them.
Bake at 325° for 2 or 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato loaf cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and water.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add next 5 ingredients, mixing just enough to moisten.
Stir in potatoes, pecans and raisins.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans (or coffee cans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans or cans and complete cooling.

title: quick chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan 11 x 7 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; let cool and pour over fruit.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip until partially set and stir in fruit and nuts. Spoon over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Sift dry ingredients and add nuts or chopped dates may be added.
Shape into rolls.
Refrigerate.
Slice thin and bake.

title: super hot bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add liquids, then mix lightly. Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar; pat into 9 X 13 greased pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: good cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine stuffing mix and melted butter.
Set aside.
Cook squash and onion until tender; drain and add chicken soup, water chestnuts, carrot, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add 3/4 of stuffing mix.
Mix well.

title: apple slices
directions: Put egg yolk in measuring cup.
Fill to 3/4 cup with milk. Blend flour and lard.
Add milk to flour.
Roll out 1/2 of dough and line jelly roll pan or small cookie sheet.
Cover with handful of crushed corn flakes.
Place sliced apples (Courtland's) on crust.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with rest of dough.
Whip egg white until frothy and brush on top of crust. Bake at 400°.
While hot, glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar and a little water, mixed.

title: cheese carrot balls
directions: Beat together carrots, cheese and Tabasco sauce.
Chill.
Form into small balls and coat with parsley.
Contains 10 calories each.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well-greased and well floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookie bars(microwave)
directions: Place butter in micro-safe bowl; cover with waxed paper. Microwave on High for 45 seconds.
Beat in sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
Combine flour, bran, oats and soda.
Stir into butter mixture.
Press half of dough into 8 x 8-inch micro-safe dish.
Shield corners with foil to prevent overcooking.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes, turning dish a quarter turn every minute. Cool before cutting.
Repeat with second half of dough.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Put chicken breasts on board and pound until thin.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Heat oil in frying pan until very hot.
Quickly brown chicken (both sides). Remove to shallow baking dish.
Take excess oil from pan.
Stir tomato sauce, basil and garlic powder in frying pan.
Heat until boiling, about 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover.
Uncover and add Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake in moderate oven until cheese is melted.

title: roasted asparagus with orange scented onions
directions: Combine onions, water, thyme, olive oil and orange rind in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir well.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until onions are golden and brown.
Remove from oven; stir in pepper.
Push onion mixture to side of dish.

title: fast peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Melt butter in an 8-inch square baking pan.
Place peaches and juice in a sauce pan and heat.
Combine flour, sugar, and milk.
Pour into baking pan with melted butter. Do not stir.
Bake for 40 - 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: cherry coffeecake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, almond flavoring, salt and baking powder.
Add flour. Save back 1 cup batter.
Spread the rest in a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Pour can of cherry pie filling over the top and dab the rest of the batter on the pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan and eggs.
Form mixture into crust in buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Cook meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat through. Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Fill with tomato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella atop and bake for 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: memphis strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl, making a well in center of mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into well.
Stir enough to dampen all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip with orange jello then add other ingredients.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in lukewarm water. Mix well the sugar, egg and Crisco. Add 3 cups or more self-rising flour and mix well. Drop by spoon. Bake in well-greased muffin pan in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done. Store remaining batter in refrigerator.

title: peter paul mound cake(three layers)
directions: Cook sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa over medium heat until it coats spoon.
Pour over cake while still hot.

title: apple butter
directions: You will need 5 quart canning jars for this recipe.

title: edward's veggie casserole
directions: Mix all cooked vegetables and mayonnaise.
Place 1/2 mixture in 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Top with cheese and margarine.
Layer again. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: elephant stewlubbock, texas
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces. (This will take about 2 months.)

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook onion and beef together until brown.
Add chili mix. Cook about 10 minutes.
Add 2 cans chili beans, 1 can diced tomatoes and 1 can warm water.
Cook about 45 minutes on low heat.

title: fruit cake cookies(very good)
directions: Mix and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: homemade flitter bread
directions: Mix together ingredients and spoon small amounts into a preheated greased iron skillet.
Fry until brown on both sides. Continue until all of the batter is used.
Add grease as needed. Can be served with syrup for pancakes or served with any meal as a bread.

title: liver appetizer
directions: Mix liver sausage, horseradish, 1 1/2 large packages cream cheese, onions, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Roll and shape into a ball.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and form into balls.
Melt Hershey bar, chocolate chips and paraffin wax together.
Dip balls in the chocolate mixture and set on wax paper to harden.
Makes about 75 to 80 balls.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, water and 4 eggs.
Pour onto a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool cake.

title: beef goulash
directions: Saute onion in shortening until translucent.
Add paprika and meat; brown.
Add seasonings.
Pour in 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer until tender, adding more water as needed.
When meat is done, uncover, and let water evaporate.
Dust with flour; stir until brown.
Add 1 more cup water and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: boiled shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp for 3 minutes in crab boil.
Drain and put ice cubes over top to cool down.
Immediately clean and devein. Combine tossed salad and shrimp. Cover with dressing.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Whip 2 cartons of whipping cream with a mixer until fluffy, then add bananas, coconut, pecans, mandarin oranges and pineapple. Use a spoon to mix ingredients.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes to 1 hour, then serve when ready.

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Place graham crackers in rows to cover baking sheet.
Boil sugar and margarine together for 2 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows until melted. Pour over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers and margarine, in large bowl. Mix well. Spoon into 2 greased 9 x 9-inch casserole dishes. Sprinkle with cracker or bread crumbs. Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until bubbly and nicely browned. Serves 16.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add egg and sugar.
Melt oleo; add oleo, flour, baking powder, baking soda and one pinch of salt.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spanish rice (beef and rice casserole)
directions: In at least a 2 1/2-quart microproof dish with cover, crumble beef and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Stir and cook for 3 more minutes.
Drain if you wish.
Make sure the cooked meat is crumbled well.
Add remaining ingredients and cut up the tomatoes and stir. Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir and cook on 20% for 10 minutes.
Stir and cook on 70% for 5 to 6 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is soft.
Let stand for a few minutes before eating or you might burn the roof of your mouth.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve on baked potatoes or use as a dip.
Good for vegetables.

title: pound cake glaze
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add almond extract.

title: easy stew
directions: In crock-pot, mix meat, soup, Lipton mix and water.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: lettuce with dressing
directions: Place lettuce in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, stir together the sugar, vinegar and light cream or sour cream until sugar dissolves and dressing is smooth.
Stir in green onion.
Just before serving, pour over lettuce.
Toss lightly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well and add to the dry mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda, then add to creamed mixture.
Mix the oatmeal and corn flakes together well, then add to mixture. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes a dishpan full!

title: orange fluff "congealed" salad
directions: Melt Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water.
Add orange juice.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Fold Dream Whip into mixture. Pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Chill overnight.

title: apple - ham casserole
directions: Arrange cooked, diced ham in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread with mustard.
Arrange cored and sliced apples over ham.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sugar and flour and sprinkle over ham. Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix sugar with bananas.
Add beaten egg, then sifted flour, baking soda and melted margarine; mix thoroughly.
Bake in muffin pans lined with large paper baking cups in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches.
Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix milk, sugar and flour; pour over butter.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mexican vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well and place in a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan sprinkle with 1 bunch green onion, monterey jack and jalapenos shredded cheese, sliced olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat refried beans with a splash of milk.
Pour enchilada sauce in a bowl wide enough to immerse tortillas in.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture, blending together.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into 2 well-oiled and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut pork (lean and fat) into small cubes.
Chop onion and garlic fine.
Dice ham and sausage.
Melt butter in heavy pot.
Add onion, garlic, pork and ham.
Brown slowly, stirring frequently. Add sausage, bay leaf, parsley, thyme and clove.
Cook 5 minutes. Add broth, Tabasco sauce and salt bringing mixture to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover and simmer gently 1/2 hour or until rice is tender. Stir often to mix well.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in spread (margarine).
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy cheese crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Allow cheddar cheese
and butter to become soft.
Cream cheese, butter and tabasco together.
Add flour and mix well.
Slowly add rice krispies until thoroughly mixed.
Form into balls,
arrange on cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Place stew meat in crock-pot.
Cover with onion soup mix. Layer sliced carrots, celery, onions and potatoes on top of meat. Add tomato soup; pour over mixture.
Add 1/2 soup can water. Cover and bake at 300° in oven or all day on low in crock-pot.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes; cool.

title: decadent mud pie
directions: Spread ice cream evenly over crust; cover and freeze until firm.
To serve, place pie slice on serving plate.
Spoon hot fudge sauce over each slice and dollop with whipped topping and sprinkle with almonds.
Serve immediately.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: creamed asparagus on toast
directions: Wash and clean asparagus, then cut into 2-inch pieces.
In medium size saucepan, cook asparagus with the water and salt until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir to melt.
Sprinkle in flour a little at a time, stirring to keep smoothly blended.
Add thyme and pepper.
Slowly stir in evaporated milk.
Return to medium heat; cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Ladle over toast.
Serve with deviled eggs, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: baked cream chicken breast
directions: In a buttered baking dish, place chicken breasts.
Cover each breast with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Cover with the cream of chicken soup that has been diluted with water.
Sprinkle with the stuffing mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Blend well.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix bread crumbs and milk and let stand until thickened, about 20 minutes.
Put ground beef and chopped onions in the mixture of bread crumbs and milk.
Add egg, salt and pepper and mix well.

title: green beans
directions: Cook and drain beans.
Add the soup and garlic croutons. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Also the chicken.
Cut chicken into bite-size. Put noodles in bottom of dish, then chicken, milk, soup and string beans.
Put bread crumbs and Velveeta cheese on top.
Bake until cheese and bread is toasted.

title: rolls
directions: Add yeast, sugar, salt and water.
Add well beaten egg.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add half of the flour and beat well.
Add oil and mix remainder of flour.
Let rise to double its bulk.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of the food coloring and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix baking soda and vinegar; fold into cake mixture.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (check after 10 minutes).

title: peter's soupy meat
directions: Fry the bacon until it's crisp, save about half the drippings. Brown the ground beef in the bacon drippings.

Meanwhile boil the celery and onion in just enough water to cover them until they're almost tender. Add the celery, onions, water and bacon to the browned beef. Stir in the ketchup, baked beans and A-1 sauce, simmer on a low heat for a short time. Serve with salad and rolls, enough for 3 people.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine all ingredients for filling.
Fill tart shells 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put through grinder the berries and oranges.
Add sugar and stir.
Refrigerate for 2 days.

title: the best baked beans!
directions: Cook the bacon just to remove the grease, not until crispy. Combine all the ingredients; add the cut pieces of bacon.
Bake in a large baking dish, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes, or cook in a crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: waldorf toss
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water. Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
If necessary, remove any unmelted ice.
Fold in fruits and celery.
Spoon into individual dishes or a bowl.
Chill until set, at least 1 hour. Make 5 cups or 10 servings.
Contains 35 calories per serving without nuts.

title: cathy's turkey scramble
directions: In medium frying pan, cook onion and turkey until done.
Add salt and pepper and a little dill weed.
Stir in cheese soup and milk.
Heat until well blended.
Serve over hot buttered rice.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift together flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, and salt in large mixing bowl.
Cut in chunk-style peanut butter and 2 tablespoons butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and eggs all at once, stirring until moistened.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Immediately brush top with 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle generously on top of bread.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions in pie crust.
Blend remaining ingredients, and pour into pie crust.
Bake for 15 minutes @ 425 degrees.
Reduce heat to 300 degrees and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Can be made ahead and baked the next day.

title: weber cooker roast
directions: Soak charcoal for 15 minutes before lighting.
Separate coals into 2 sections, 8-inches apart (circular cooking).
Light coals and let them get hot.
Cover roast with Worcestershire sauce, seasoning salt, black pepper and garlic salt.
Cover with foil and let cook for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: t j's strawberry pie
directions: Place berries in 2 baked pie shells.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick and clear.
Add jello; cool slightly.
Pour mixture over strawberries.

title: swedish crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add butter and crumble with your hands until fine.
Save 1/2
cup
for top. Mix well, then add baking powder, eggs,
milk and vanilla and lemon extracts. Put the 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 8-inch square pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Rinse vegetables under hot water to remove ice.
Melt butter and cheese, stirring constantly until creamy and smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Add bread crumbs and stir all together.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Take seeds from persimmons and mash. Add cream, egg, sugar and flour.
Mix until thickness of corn bread batter.
Bake at 350° until center is set and knife comes out clean.
Do not overbake. This will be cake like. Serve with whipped cream.

title: buttermilk cookie salad
directions: Mix pudding with buttermilk and add whipped topping.
Drain fruit and add to pudding mixture.
Just before serving, break cookies into small pieces and add to mixture.
Other fruits can be substituted.

title: portuguese eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Put yolks in bowl and thoroughly blend with 4 tablespoons butter, herbs, salt and pepper to taste. Spoon the mixture into the egg whites.
Spread tomatoes over the bottom of a baking dish and place stuffed eggs on them.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and stir in the flour.
Cook and stir for 3 minutes.
Add the tomato juice and milk.
Stir and cook until smooth and thick.
Pour around and over the eggs.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: biscochitos(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar and anise seed.
Add beaten eggs and blend until fluffy. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add enough liquid to make a stiff dough.
Knead slightly and roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters and top with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on rack. Do not overbake.

title: trash
directions: Mix Chex and pretzels in large bowl.
Mix and melt bacon grease, butter, sauces and pepper in pan until warm.
Pour over Chex and pretzels, mixing well.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool and keep in covered container.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Beat together egg and milk.
Dip meat in egg mixture and then in cracker crumbs.
In heavy skillet, heat oil.
Add coated meat.
Brown well on both sides, turning once.
Reduce heat and cook, covered, for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Add salt and pepper.

title: dorothy's corn casserole
directions: Mix all, except crushed crackers.
The last five minutes, top with crackers.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake in a 7 x 7-inch pan for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate-cherry torte
directions: Grease and lightly flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, prepare the cake mix batter according to the package directions.
Turn the batter into the prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in the pans for 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from pans; cool thoroughly.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.
This makes a real thick chili.

title: no knead bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Measure sugar, salt, shortening and 1 1/2 cups water in large bowl. Beat in yeast and eggs.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough and mix well.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down, cover lightly and refrigerate.
Remove dough from refrigerator.
Shape rolls and let rise until doubled.
Bake in 400° oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough can be kept for 3 or 4 days in refrigerator.

title: lemon pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
In saucepan, add sifted mixture with egg yolks (save whites in small bowl), water, lemon juice and butter.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
(If color isn't yellow enough, add 1 to 2 drops yellow food coloring.) Cool slightly; pour into baked pie shell.

title: crissfield maryland elks wives' sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Chill several hours, better overnight.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: "skinny soup"
directions: Put on lid and cook until tender.
Delicious.

title: roast turkey in peanut butter
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare turkey for roasting.
Combine peanut butter, flour, paprika, salt, celery salt and pepper.
Stir together until blended, adding enough milk to make a medium paste. Spread paste over entire turkey, covering well.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Add 1 cup water to pan.
Bake for 3 to 4 hours. Baste every 30 minutes with pan juices.
If you stuff the turkey, roast 45 minutes longer.

title: black bean dip
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in the bowl of a food processor; pulse until just chunky.
Transfer to a medium size bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Taste and adjust seasoning with more lime juice or cayenne.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken livers and barley
directions: Heat 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes.
Add barley and brown lightly.
Stir in bouillon.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until barley is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Saute chicken livers in the remaining butter.
Season to taste, then stir into barley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick noodles and ham
directions: Microwave 1 1/2 c. water until boiling, stir in milk, butter, noodles and sauce and ham.
Cover and cook on high 5-6 minutes, stir only once.
Add pea pods, cook 2-3 minutes; stir only once. Let stand for 5 minutes and serve.

title: hot steak subs
directions: Heat oil.
Cook steak, onion, garlic and oregano.
Stir in gravy.
Spoon 1/4 cup beef onto each piece of hard roll.
Top with lettuce, cheese and tomato and top of roll.

title: jalapeno pepper corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp boil
directions: In an 8-quart saucepan, add 5 quarts of water, 1 can of beer and crab boil seasoning pouch.
Bring to a boil and add corn-on-the-cob.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Cut link sausage into 1-inch pieces and drop into boiling corn and cook for 10 minutes. Drop shrimp last and cook for a few minutes until shrimp are pink and done.
Careful not to overcook shrimp or they will be tough. Drain entire mixture and serve immediately with Heinz seafood cocktail sauce.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix butter, oil and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chilled strawberry soup(low fat and tasty)
directions: Blend all ingredients well and serve chilled with fresh strawberries on top.

title: quick, easy chocolate chip pie
directions: Divide nuts and chips in bottom of two unbaked pie shells. Over this, pour mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until set in center of pie.
Yields 2 pies (use half of recipe for 1 pie).

title: veggie casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until crisp-tender.
Drain. Arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Put the cream of chicken soup over vegetables.
Cover with 2 cups grated cheese and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
During the last 10 minutes, put the can of onion rings on top.

title: oyster orgasms
directions: Stir every 10 to 20 minutes until well combined.

title: barbecued rabbit
directions: Roll meat pieces in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in heavy frying pan or roaster.
Brown meat on all sides, moderate heat, about 20 minutes.

title: mile high strawberry cloud
directions: Mix together with electric mixer until crumbly.
With hands, press dough into ball.
Press dough in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: egg casserole
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, salt and soda. Stir in egg and undrained fruit cocktail. Pour into greased 10 x 7-inch baking pan. Blend brown sugar and nuts together and sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: *yogurt chevre
directions: Pour the yogurt in a double layer of cheesecloth. Tie at top and drain for a few hours or overnight until yogurt is consistency of cream cheese.
Add the garlic and spices.
Mix well.
Put in a small crock overnight for flavors to blend. Serve with crackers.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Line 9 inch pie pan with pastry. Cream butter, salt and sugar. Add lemon juice, rind and egg yolks; beat until light and fluffy. Mix flour with small amount of milk and stir until smooth. Add remaining milk and combine with creamed mixture. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour into pastry shell. Bake at 450 degrees 10 minutes, reduce temperature to 325 degrees and bake 45-50 minutes longer, until firm. Makes 1 deep dish 9 inch pie.

title: fruit pizza topping
directions: Blend cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Spread on crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, salt, water, orange juice and lemon juice over low heat until thick.
Chill.
Spoon over fruit.

title: roasted salmon with vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium bowl, combine oil, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Quarter the potatoes.
(If using large potatoes, cut them into 3/4-inch cubes.)
Slice the carrots on the diagonal into 2-inch pieces.
Cut the scallions into 1-inch pieces.
Cut the mushrooms into halves.
(If the mushrooms are large, quarter them.)

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots for 10 minutes and dice.
Add all other items and mix well.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: hot turkey sandwiches
directions: Remove skin from turkey.
Rub with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Put turkey in roasting bag and put in cake pan or roaster. Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour this mixture over the turkey in the bag.

title: short-cut cabbage rolls
directions: Spread cabbage in large casserole dish.
Mix rice, pork sausage, seasonings and sauerkraut.
Spread over cabbage.
Mix tomato paste with water.
Pour over mixture.
Bake covered 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove from oven.
Spread sour cream on top. Spread raw biscuits and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until brown at 400°.

title: jello salad
directions: Empty pineapple and juice into large bowl.
Pour strawberry Jell-O over; stir.
Mix in other ingredients and chill.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, until golden brown.

title: soft drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat oleo, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy, then add sour cream and vanilla.
Beat in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Drop batter by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown on bottom.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a large skillet.
Fry chicken until brown.
Drain and place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: You will need a 9-inch pie plate.

title: pecan pie
directions: In bowl, using mixer at medium speed, beat first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on rack. Makes 8 servings.

title: dream puffs
directions: Add butter and salt to boiling water and stir over medium heat until boils.
Reduce heat and add flour and beat until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat and add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Put 1 teaspoon of puff mixture on baking sheet and bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for another 5 minutes.

title: orange sauce
directions: Cook about 25 minutes.
Great on pancakes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix with a fork.
Pour into a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate overnight.

title: jerky
directions: In a container, mix all seasonings.
Dissolve in water.
Have venison cut in 3/8-inch strips.
Place the strips of meat in the marinade; be sure meat is completely covered.
Let set overnight, turning if necessary.
Lay marinated strips on oven rack.
Cook for 6 to 8 hours at 150°.
They get crispier the longer they bake. Store finished jerky in Ziploc bags or other airtight containers to seal in freshness.
Jerky will keep up to 2 years.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs together.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
